11
00:03:26,376 --> 00:03:31,013
(聖米爾伊格奡肅磲 藥劑師亞歷山大·雷諾)

12
00:03:32,082 --> 00:03:36,314
在這黑暗的時刻,在這黑暗的夜堙K…
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In this darkest hour, in the gloom of night...{\r}

13
00:03:36,553 --> 00:03:38,441
……我們沒必要絕望
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...we must not despair.{\r}

14
00:03:39,290 --> 00:03:43,715
(皮爾·路易斯·羅蘭德)

15
00:03:39,991 --> 00:03:44,746
我們要保持我們最初的信念,堅定不移!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let us keep our faith intact,unswerving!{\r}

16
00:03:45,563 --> 00:03:47,326
為了我們每個人……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}For each of us...{\r}

17
00:03:48,567 --> 00:03:51,365
……自由正在來臨
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...deliverance is coming.{\r}

18
00:03:56,243 --> 00:04:00,277
(沃納·普拉斯凱少校)
(德軍第三五二海防師)

19
00:04:19,769 --> 00:04:23,000
我們要在整個海岸布下地雷和障礙物
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We need mines and obstacles along the whole coast.{\r}

20
00:04:23,273 --> 00:04:26,197
包括每一個海灘,每一個沙丘……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}At every beach, on every dune...{\r}

21
00:04:26,477 --> 00:04:28,707
……每一塊礁石
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...on every rock.{\r}

22
00:04:28,913 --> 00:04:31,006
已經佈置了多少？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How many have been installed?{\r}

23
00:04:31,282 --> 00:04:33,807
四百萬,陸軍元帥
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Four million, Herr Field Marshal.{\r}

24
00:04:34,286 --> 00:04:36,413
五月必須達到六百萬
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-
It has to be six million by May.{\r}

25
00:04:34,486 --> 00:04:36,413
五月必須達到六百萬
(德軍西線Ｂ集團軍群總司令 埃爾溫·隆美爾陸軍元帥)

26
00:04:36,413 --> 00:04:40,645
(德軍西線Ｂ集團軍群總司令 埃爾溫·隆美爾陸軍元帥)
－六百萬
－我們的人一刻未停
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Six million.
-Our men are constantly deployed.{\r}

27
00:04:40,827 --> 00:04:43,193
根本沒有提及休整的事
(德軍第十五集團軍司令 　漢斯·馮·薩爾穆特上將)
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There's no point in even discussing rest.{\r}

28
00:04:43,362 --> 00:04:46,661
－部隊已經精疲力竭了
－親愛的馮·薩爾穆特……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-The troops are completely exhausted.
-My dear Herr von Salmuth...{\r}

29
00:04:46,833 --> 00:04:48,824
……你更願意讓你的部下……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...which would your troops rather be...{\r}

30
00:04:49,103 --> 00:04:51,094
……筋疲力盡還是喪命？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...exhausted or dead?{\r}

31
00:04:51,338 --> 00:04:53,329
看看這,各位
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Just look at it, gentlemen.{\r}

32
00:04:53,874 --> 00:04:55,899
如此寧靜詳和
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How calm, how peaceful it is.{\r}

33
00:04:56,344 --> 00:05:00,007
橫亙在英國和歐陸之間的這片水域……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A strip of water between England and the Continent...{\r}

34
00:05:00,315 --> 00:05:02,237
……盟軍和我們各據一方
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...between the Allies and us.{\r}

35
00:05:03,118 --> 00:05:08,249
但是在那頭平靜的地平線上,潛伏著一頭怪獸
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But beyond that peaceful horizon, a monster waits.{\r}

36
00:05:08,557 --> 00:05:12,288
整裝待發的部隊,軍艦,和飛機……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A coiled spring of men, ships and planes...{\r}

37
00:05:12,696 --> 00:05:15,620
……想要一舉擊潰我們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...straining to be released against us.{\r}

38
00:05:16,900 --> 00:05:20,996
但沒有一名盟軍士兵能登上這片海灘
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But not a single Allied soldier shall reach the shore.{\r}

39
00:05:21,172 --> 00:05:25,199
沒有一名盎格魯美利堅人能涉足這片海灘
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Not a single Anglo-American shall set foot on the beaches.{\r}

40
00:05:25,843 --> 00:05:30,268
無論這次入侵來自何時何地……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Whenever or wherever this invasion may come, gentlemen...{\r}

41
00:05:31,150 --> 00:05:35,814
……我都會將敵軍殲滅在海岸邊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...I shall destroy the enemy there, at the water's edge.{\r}

42
00:05:37,056 --> 00:05:38,580
相信我,各位
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Believe me, gentlemen.{\r}

43
00:05:38,858 --> 00:05:42,282
入侵的頭二十四小時將成為關鍵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The first 24 hours of the invasion will be decisive.{\r}

44
00:05:42,730 --> 00:05:47,429
對於盟軍和我軍來說,都將是最漫長的一天……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}For the Allies as well as the Germans,
it will be the longest day...{\r}

45
00:05:49,436 --> 00:05:50,801
……最漫長的一天
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...the longest day.{\r}

46
00:05:51,237 --> 00:06:00,203
片名:最長的一天

47
00:06:15,166 --> 00:06:19,843
(德軍西線總司令部參謀長 岡瑟爾·布魯門特堹S少將)
(德軍西線總司令部 法國巴黎郊區)

48
00:06:25,611 --> 00:06:28,444
－魏爾倫(Paul Verlaine)的詩？
－是的,第一節(《秋歌》)
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-The poem by Verlaine?
-Yes, the first verse.{\r}

49
00:06:28,715 --> 00:06:30,148
倒回重放!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Play it back!{\r}

50
00:06:30,884 --> 00:06:32,806
安靜!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Silence!{\r}

51
00:06:34,588 --> 00:06:39,045
(德軍第十五集團軍反間諜處處長 海默斯·梅耶中校)

52
00:06:37,728 --> 00:06:39,146
倫敦廣播:

53
00:06:40,628 --> 00:06:43,756
法國人致其同胞的公告
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Frenchmen speaking to their countrymen.{\r}

54
00:06:44,933 --> 00:06:48,755
這是一些與個人有關的口信
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Here are some personal messages.{\r}

55
00:06:51,908 --> 00:06:55,639
「秋天的小提琴那長長的嗚咽」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"The long sobs of the violins of autumn. "{\r}

56
00:06:56,079 --> 00:06:57,137
重複
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I repeat:{\r}

57
00:06:57,413 --> 00:07:01,144
「秋天的小提琴那長長的嗚咽」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"The long sobs of the violins of autumn. "{\r}

58
00:07:01,652 --> 00:07:05,281
有沒有通知所有指揮部？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Have you notified all commands?{\r}

59
00:07:15,468 --> 00:07:20,292
如果柏林方面是對的,那我們截聽到第二節時……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If Berlin is right, when we intercept the second verse...{\r}

60
00:07:20,539 --> 00:07:24,805
……就表示入侵將在二十四小時內發動
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...it will mean the invasion will come within 24 hours.{\r}

61
00:07:25,612 --> 00:07:27,409
給我看看第二節
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Give me the text of the second verse.{\r}

62
00:07:43,666 --> 00:07:47,090
「用單調的憂鬱刺傷我的心」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"Wounds my heart with a monotonous languor."{\r}

63
00:07:49,673 --> 00:07:53,962
去年我們截聽了數以百計的信息,數以百計!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We've intercepted hundreds of messages in the last year, hundreds!{\r}

64
00:07:54,178 --> 00:07:57,375
我一而再再而三地下令戒備
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've ordered alerts again and again.{\r}

65
00:07:57,581 --> 00:08:01,642
為什麼這首詩會比其他信息有更多意味？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Why should this poem mean more than other messages?{\r}

66
00:08:01,853 --> 00:08:03,309
告訴我
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Tell me this:{\r}

67
00:08:03,522 --> 00:08:08,186
它會提供任何敵軍何時何地入侵的線索嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Does it give us any clue as to where they will land and when?{\r}

68
00:08:08,361 --> 00:08:10,727
當然不會
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course it doesn't.{\r}

69
00:08:11,030 --> 00:08:13,555
有五十萬軍隊由我指揮
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I have half a million men under my command.{\r}

70
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:19,760
如果我不斷下令戒備的話,該如何維持軍紀……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How can I maintain discipline
if I keep my troops on the alert...{\r}

71
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:24,700
……就因為柏林一對傻瓜截聽到的一首詩？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...just because a pair of nitwits in Berlin intercept a poem?{\r}

72
00:08:26,348 --> 00:08:28,873
不,布魯門特堹S,不用戒備
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, Blumentritt, no alert.{\r}

73
00:08:31,019 --> 00:08:33,283
尤其是在這種天氣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And especially not in this weather.{\r}

74
00:08:34,623 --> 00:08:36,921
－還有事嗎？
－沒有,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Anything else?
-No, sir.{\r}

75
00:08:55,147 --> 00:08:56,739
早,陸軍元帥
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Good morning, field marshal.{\r}

76
00:08:57,049 --> 00:08:58,880
－有情況嗎？
－沒有什麼要緊的情況
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Any news?
-Nothing important.{\r}

77
00:08:59,051 --> 00:09:01,884
昨天下午加萊遭到了轟炸
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fighter bombers hit the Pas-de-Calais yesterday afternoon.{\r}

78
00:09:02,088 --> 00:09:05,421
昨晚沒發生其他事,風暴要來了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing much happened last night. The storm.{\r}

79
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:09,447
我關心的只是今早這場風暴
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's all I'm interested in this morning, the storm.{\r}

80
00:09:09,662 --> 00:09:15,157
不知從哪來的,把我的玫瑰都吹壞了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It came from nowhere, blew my roses to bits.{\r}

81
00:09:16,437 --> 00:09:19,031
海峽上的浪有五英尺高……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There are 5-foot waves in the Channel...{\r}

82
00:09:19,274 --> 00:09:22,869
……風速每小時三十到四十英里
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and winds of 30 to 40 miles per hour.{\r}

83
00:09:23,311 --> 00:09:25,575
以六月而言……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}For the month of June...{\r}

84
00:09:25,815 --> 00:09:28,306
……是二十年來最惡劣的海峽風暴
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...it's the worst Channel storm in 20 years.{\r}

85
00:09:28,584 --> 00:09:30,950
我到貝希特斯加登晉見元首的事怎麼樣了？
(隆美爾打算請求希特勒調遣兩個裝甲師到諾曼底)
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}My appointment at Berchtesgaden?{\r}

86
00:09:31,587 --> 00:09:34,681
約德爾將軍今天要去見元首……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}General Jodl will see the Fuhrer today...{\r}

87
00:09:34,925 --> 00:09:37,655
……並為您安排晉見
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and confirm the appointment for you.{\r}

88
00:09:39,863 --> 00:09:42,559
您還是要按計劃去回德國嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Will you still go to Germany as planned?{\r}

89
00:09:42,767 --> 00:09:45,361
還能找到更好的時間嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Can you think of a better time?{\r}

90
00:09:46,404 --> 00:09:50,966
這種天氣看來要持續到下星期
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The weather is expected to continue like this for another week.{\r}

91
00:09:53,279 --> 00:10:00,967
( 英         國 )
