－他是個將軍的傳令兵
－快來,快來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-He's an orderly for some general.
-Move it. Move it.{\r}

109
00:11:29,721 --> 00:11:31,052
嘿,哈奇
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, Hutchy!{\r}

110
00:11:31,390 --> 00:11:33,346
哈奇,我有事要問你
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hutchy, I want to ask you something.{\r}

111
00:11:34,192 --> 00:11:35,750
嘿,哈奇森……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, Hutchinson...{\r}

112
00:11:36,062 --> 00:11:39,725
……如果是重要行動,會讓我們寫信回家嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...do you think they'd let me writehome?
If it was really important?{\r}

113
00:11:39,933 --> 00:11:42,959
不可能,夥計,得保密
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Not likely, mate. Security.{\r}

114
00:11:43,202 --> 00:11:45,432
老丘吉爾並不相信我們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't think old Churchill trusts us.{\r}

115
00:11:45,639 --> 00:11:48,301
是寫給我太太,她快生了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's the wife, you see. She's going to have a baby.{\r}

116
00:11:48,576 --> 00:11:49,702
第一個孩子，是吧？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Your first, is it?{\r}

117
00:11:49,910 --> 00:11:53,141
不是我的,但我很擔心她
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, it's not mine, but I'm dead worried about her.{\r}

118
00:11:53,415 --> 00:11:55,576
她身體不是很好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}She's not too strong, you see.{\r}

119
00:12:21,045 --> 00:12:23,775
老兄,那兒真臭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Man, that stink.{\r}

120
00:12:24,516 --> 00:12:28,441
有柴油,臨時廁所,嘔吐物
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Diesel oil, backed-up toilets, vomit.{\r}

121
00:12:29,321 --> 00:12:31,881
沒有地方安置病號
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And there ain't no place left to get sick in.{\r}

122
00:12:32,726 --> 00:12:34,421
嘔吐袋都滿了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The puke bags is full.{\r}

123
00:12:34,628 --> 00:12:36,926
消防桶也吐滿了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The fire buckets is full.{\r}

124
00:12:38,332 --> 00:12:40,926
只剩下鋼盔還能用
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All we got left is our helmets.{\r}

125
00:12:43,337 --> 00:12:44,793
六月
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}June.{\r}

126
00:12:48,043 --> 00:12:51,672
我老頭子每年六月總是帶我去露營……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Every June my old man used to take me camping...{\r}

127
00:12:53,850 --> 00:12:56,410
……在藍嶺上邊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...up in the Blue Mountains.{\r}

128
00:12:57,820 --> 00:13:00,653
我們整天都打獵釣魚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We'd hunt and fish all day long.{\r}

129
00:13:02,493 --> 00:13:04,154
到了晚上……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And at night...{\r}

130
00:13:05,262 --> 00:13:08,117
……我們就睡在星光之下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...we'd sleep out under the stars.{\r}

131
00:13:10,802 --> 00:13:12,895
連毛毯都不用
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Didn't even need a blanket.{\r}

132
00:13:17,710 --> 00:13:19,109
六月
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}June.{\r}

133
00:13:24,317 --> 00:13:26,945
又是風,又是雨
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Wind and rain. Wind and rain.{\r}

134
00:13:27,187 --> 00:13:28,552
還有完沒完？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't it ever stop?{\r}

135
00:13:28,822 --> 00:13:31,916
看,老爹,我只想著出發
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, Dad, all I want to do is get going.{\r}

136
00:13:32,126 --> 00:13:36,324
管它風還是雨,哪怕降落在艾菲爾鐵塔上都行
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Wind or no wind. Even if we land in Paris on the Eiffel Tower.{\r}

137
00:13:36,631 --> 00:13:39,020
－想想看……
－中校找我們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Come to think of it--
-Colonel wants us.{\r}

138
00:13:39,201 --> 00:13:40,930
所有人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All of us.{\r}

139
00:13:49,212 --> 00:13:55,049
(第五○五團第二營營長 本傑明·范迪沃特中校)
(美軍第八十二空降師)

140
00:13:49,713 --> 00:13:53,444
我接到通知,計劃有變
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've notified the adjutant, change in schedule.{\r}

141
00:13:53,616 --> 00:13:55,049
今天碰頭會之後……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}After briefing session today...{\r}

142
00:13:55,219 --> 00:13:58,780
……所有部隊都要參與地面作戰佈署
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...all troops will participate
in ground tactics and deployment.{\r}

143
00:13:59,056 --> 00:14:00,978
在這種天氣嗎,頭？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In this weather, sir?{\r}

144
00:14:02,160 --> 00:14:05,652
當然,哈丁,你能保證降落在法國時……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course, Harding,
if you can ensure that we'll land in France...{\r}

145
00:14:05,897 --> 00:14:08,491
－……是大晴天嗎？
－我不是這意思
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-...in sunshine and dry weather.
-Didn't mean that.{\r}

146
00:14:08,734 --> 00:14:11,100
－那是什麼意思？
－不是指天氣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What did you mean?
-It isn't the weather.{\r}

147
00:14:11,270 --> 00:14:14,330
是等待時間,大伙都等不及了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's the waiting. These men are itching to go.{\r}

148
00:14:14,574 --> 00:14:16,963
我想用不著我來提醒你……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't think I have to remind you...{\r}

149
00:14:17,243 --> 00:14:20,576
……這場戰爭已經持續將近五年了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...that this war has been going on for almost five years.{\r}

150
00:14:20,814 --> 00:14:23,180
半個歐洲遭到侵佔
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Half of Europe has been overrun and occupied.{\r}

151
00:14:23,417 --> 00:14:25,874
我們是屬於新來的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're comparative newcomers.{\r}

152
00:14:26,087 --> 00:14:30,376
英國從一九四○年起就一直面臨入侵，如芒在背
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}England's gone through a blitz
with a knife at her throat since 1940.{\r}

153
00:14:30,592 --> 00:14:34,824
我相信他們也迫不及待地想要反攻
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I am quite sure that they too are impatient and itching to go.{\r}

154
00:14:35,097 --> 00:14:36,894
說得夠清楚了嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Do I make myself clear?{\r}

155
00:14:37,133 --> 00:14:38,691
是的,頭,很清楚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir. Quite clear.{\r}

156
00:14:39,602 --> 00:14:42,696
有三百萬人駐紮在這個島上
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Three million men penned up on this island.{\r}

157
00:14:42,939 --> 00:14:46,636
像這樣的兵營遍及整個英格蘭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All over England, in staging areas like this.{\r}

158
00:14:46,877 --> 00:14:51,007
我們正處在有史以來最重要時刻的前沿
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're on the threshold of the most crucial day of our times.{\r}

159
00:14:51,282 --> 00:14:53,443
三百萬人在這……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Three million men out there...{\r}

160
00:14:53,684 --> 00:14:58,542
……蓄勢待發,就為了這一刻
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...keyed up, and waiting for that big step-off.{\r}

161
00:15:00,993 --> 00:15:03,120
實際上不止是他們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They aren't exactly alone.{\r}

162
00:15:04,664 --> 00:15:07,656
通知部隊,下午二點前收拾好行裝
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Notify the men. Full packs and equipment, 1400 hours.{\r}

163
00:15:07,934 --> 00:15:09,026
是,頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir.{\r}

164
00:15:09,669 --> 00:15:12,832
他們說都能派上用場
－
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They said they have both issues available.{\r}

165
00:15:10,134 --> 00:15:12,832
他們說都能派上用場
(美軍第二十九步兵師副師長 諾曼·Ｄ·科塔准將)

166
00:15:12,833 --> 00:15:15,527
(美軍第二十九步兵師副師長 諾曼·Ｄ·科塔准將)

167
00:15:13,507 --> 00:15:17,136
我更喜歡這一款,比較寬鬆
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I prefer this type. It allows you more freedom.{\r}

168
00:15:17,311 --> 00:15:20,474
登陸後脫起來比較快
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Quicker to get rid of when we hit the beach.{\r}

169
00:15:21,183 --> 00:15:23,139
－怎麼樣？
－定下來了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Well?
-It's on.{\r}

170
00:15:24,085 --> 00:15:26,144
今晚,照計劃進行
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Tonight, as scheduled.{\r}

171
00:15:26,823 --> 00:15:29,189
－只要天氣不更糟
－還能更糟嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-If the weather isn't worse.
-How worse can it get?{\r}

172
00:15:29,392 --> 00:15:32,589
艾克召集高層在九點三十開會
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Ike has called a high-level conference for 9:30.{\r}

173
00:15:32,829 --> 00:15:37,061
我不是艾森豪威爾,我是副師長
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I am not Eisenhower. I am an assistant division commander.{\r}

174
00:15:37,334 --> 00:15:41,998
我什麼都不管,但他不能再取消
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know from nothing, but he can't call it off again.{\r}

175
00:15:46,077 --> 00:15:47,510
弗蘭克,關掉那玩意
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Frank, turn that thing off.{\r}

176
00:15:47,712 --> 00:15:50,101
四千艘船都已裝備好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Four thousand ships loaded for bear.{\r}

177
00:15:50,349 --> 00:15:51,907
部隊做好了出發準備
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Troops ready to go.{\r}

178
00:15:52,084 --> 00:15:53,949
一萬一千架飛機在隨時待命
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Eleven thousand planes on the line.{\r}

179
00:15:54,153 --> 00:15:57,748
加上一萬八千傘兵和天知道有多少的滑翔機
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Eighteen thousand paratroopers.
God only knows how many gliders.{\r}

180
00:15:58,024 --> 00:16:00,049
諾爾,放鬆點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Norm, relax.{\r}

181
00:16:02,062 --> 00:16:04,758
皇家空軍說大風隨時可能停止
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}RAF says the gale can stop as suddenly as it began.{\r}

182
00:16:04,998 --> 00:16:07,296
所以他們前天昨天都這麼對我們說
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}So they told us yesterday and the day before.{\r}

183
00:16:07,535 --> 00:16:09,025
諾爾
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, Norm.{\r}

184
00:16:10,371 --> 00:16:12,259
我們所有人……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're all of us just as...{\r}

185
00:16:12,540 --> 00:16:16,032
……都和你一樣盼著開始行動
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...dedicated to this thing as you are,
just as anxious to get going.{\r}

186
00:16:16,245 --> 00:16:18,236
也包括艾克
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And that includes Ike.{\r}

187
00:16:18,447 --> 00:16:21,405
如果他再次取消行動,一定有他的理由
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now if he calls it off again, he knows what he's doing.{\r}

188
00:16:21,618 --> 00:16:24,314
他當然有理由,這我知道
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course he does. I know that.{\r}

189
00:16:24,520 --> 00:16:28,286
我考慮的是突擊部隊,一共二十萬人……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm just thinking about those assault troops.
200,000 of them...{\r}

190
00:16:28,525 --> 00:16:31,881
……呆在船上,恐怕吐得七葷八素了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...out there on those ships. They're probably seasick as hell.{\r}

191
00:16:32,129 --> 00:16:35,917
有些人在「澡盆子」塈b了都快三天了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Some of those men have been on
those tubs for almost three days.{\r}

192
00:16:36,735 --> 00:16:38,396
行動吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I say go.{\r}

193
00:16:38,637 --> 00:16:41,231
行動,管它天氣不天氣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go. Weather or no weather.{\r}

194
00:16:43,275 --> 00:16:44,469
不!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No!{\r}

195
00:16:46,078 --> 00:16:47,943
我押一百!來吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A hundred on the bone! Let's go.{\r}

196
00:16:48,147 --> 00:16:52,106
－給我五十塊,我輸光了
－我手氣也不怎麼樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Hey, give me 50 bucks. I'm busted.
-I'm not doing so good myself.{\r}

197
00:17:01,296 --> 00:17:03,025
借我五十塊行嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, lend me 50 bucks?{\r}

198
00:17:08,270 --> 00:17:10,795
－借我二十塊行嗎？
－去死吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Lend me 20 bucks?
-Drop dead.{\r}

199
00:17:16,947 --> 00:17:18,312
借我十塊行嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Lend me 10?{\r}

200
00:17:25,656 --> 00:17:27,180
－五十塊一注
－我有
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Fifty on a bet.
-I got it.{\r}

201
00:17:27,458 --> 00:17:29,449
一,二,三,四,五
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}One, two, three, four, five.{\r}

202
00:17:29,694 --> 00:17:31,355
五十!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fifty!{\r}

203
00:17:33,465 --> 00:17:35,353
讓我聽聽,讓我聽聽
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me hear it, let me hear it.{\r}

204
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:39,058
－五和二,四和三
－六!這樣才對嘛!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Five and two, four and three.
-Six! That's the way we go!{\r}

205
00:17:39,305 --> 00:17:42,729
一直是七點的,邪門,真邪門
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Seven points in a row.It ain't logical, it just ain't logical.{\r}

206
00:17:42,976 --> 00:17:47,868
－這把押一百塊
－一百塊,再加二十
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-There's 100 out there.
-A hundred dollars, $20.{\r}

207
00:17:48,115 --> 00:17:49,639
還有要押嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Anything open?{\r}

208
00:17:49,850 --> 00:17:51,806
－再來四十
－再來四十
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Forty more.
-Forty more.{\r}

209
00:17:52,019 --> 00:17:53,680
你有賭注了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You got a bet.{\r}

210
00:17:54,489 --> 00:17:58,016
－好了,你他媽……
－等等,等一下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Okay, you mother-loving--
-Just a minute. Wait a minute.{\r}

211
00:17:58,994 --> 00:18:00,552
拿著,用這個
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Here you are. Use this.{\r}

212
00:18:00,763 --> 00:18:03,220
－你不會以為……
－沒什麼以為
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-You don't think l'd--
-I don't think anything.{\r}

213
00:18:03,499 --> 00:18:06,764
我只是想聽到杯子發出的聲音
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I just like to hear the sound when it comes out of the cup.{\r}

214
00:18:08,638 --> 00:18:10,629
就這樣,搖吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's it. Shake it.{\r}

215
00:18:12,009 --> 00:18:15,467
好了,讓我看看你的運氣,來,開吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay. Let me see what you do with it now.  Go ahead. Shoot.{\r}

216
00:18:15,712 --> 00:18:17,236
－是什麼？
－沒什麼
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What is it?
-Nothing.{\r}

217
00:18:18,016 --> 00:18:19,381
－七!
－正是我想要的!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Seven!
-That's what I wanted!{\r}

218
00:18:19,650 --> 00:18:21,880
是誰拿這杯子來的？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Who put this cup in the game?{\r}

219
00:18:22,153 --> 00:18:24,883
－下一把,誰來擲？
－我押一百塊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Next shooter. Who's coming up?
-I'll go $100.{\r}

220
00:18:25,090 --> 00:18:27,684
他下一百,有誰接盤？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He's shooting 100.
Who's got it?{\r}

221
00:18:27,893 --> 00:18:30,259
－看好你的賭注
－一百塊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Watch your side bets.
-A hundred dollars.{\r}

222
00:18:31,898 --> 00:18:34,594
有我的信嗎,舒爾茨的？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You got a letter for me. Schultz, huh?{\r}

223
00:18:36,603 --> 00:18:37,968
有,在這
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah, that's it.{\r}

224
00:18:38,571 --> 00:18:39,765
謝謝,夥計
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thanks, buddy.{\r}

225
00:18:48,683 --> 00:18:52,915
－你贏了多少？
－不多,才兩千五多一點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-How much did you take him for?
-Not much. Just a hair over 2500.{\r}

226
00:18:53,622 --> 00:18:55,487
－兩千五？
－對
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Twenty-five hundred?
-Yeah.{\r}

227
00:18:55,725 --> 00:18:58,091
哦,夥計,兩千五？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, man, 2500?{\r}

228
00:18:59,295 --> 00:19:01,388
現在贏錢可不太妙
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's too bad you had to win it now.{\r}

229
00:19:01,898 --> 00:19:03,126
「現在」是什麼意思？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you mean, now?{\r}

230
00:19:03,333 --> 00:19:06,427
要是今晚行動你拿這些有什麼用？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Suppose we take off tonight.  What will you do with it?{\r}

231
00:19:07,304 --> 00:19:11,968
五百塊用來在巴黎喝酒泡馬子
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Five I take with me to Paris to blow on the broads and wine.{\r}

232
00:19:12,177 --> 00:19:14,600
一千塊留在這等回來再花
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A thou I leave here for seed when I get back.{\r}

233
00:19:14,879 --> 00:19:16,972
剩下的寄給我媽媽
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And the rest I send to my mother.{\r}

234
00:19:39,340 --> 00:19:42,798
哦,夥計,兩千五,還有巴黎
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, man, 2500. And in Paris.{\r}

235
00:19:43,112 --> 00:19:44,670
你總這麼好運
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You always was lucky.{\r}

236
00:19:44,847 --> 00:19:46,769
記得在布拉格堡那晚嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, remember that night in Fort Bragg?{\r}

237
00:19:49,886 --> 00:19:51,217
記得
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I remember it.{\r}

238
00:19:51,654 --> 00:19:56,114
知道嗎,我想我該過去給自己撈上一把
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You know, I think I sneak over there
and give it a big whang myself.{\r}

239
00:19:56,393 --> 00:19:58,315
幹嘛不呢？沒什麼可輸的嘛？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Why not? What's to lose?{\r}

240
00:20:01,999 --> 00:20:03,455
該死
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Damn it.{\r}

241
00:20:05,270 --> 00:20:08,159
他幹嘛提布拉格堡？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Why did he have to mention Fort Bragg?{\r}

242
00:20:10,475 --> 00:20:13,672
那次擲骰子我手氣很好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I was lucky, all right, in that crap game.{\r}

243
00:20:16,149 --> 00:20:18,572
第二天空降就把腿弄斷了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Next day I break my leg in a jump.{\r}

244
00:20:19,153 --> 00:20:21,348
做了兩個月牽引
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And two months in traction.{\r}

245
00:20:33,168 --> 00:20:36,558
兩千五百美元
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Twenty-five hundred dollars.{\r}

246
00:20:38,741 --> 00:20:41,801
我這輩子從沒有過這麼多錢
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's more money I ever had in my whole life.{\r}

247
00:20:46,550 --> 00:20:48,074
我知道
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I know.{\r}

248
00:20:49,686 --> 00:20:52,314
夥計,我知道
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Man, I just know.{\r}

249
00:21:04,469 --> 00:21:09,031
我倒想知道輸掉兩千五百美元要多久
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I wonder how long it takes to lose $2500.{\r}

250
00:21:12,512 --> 00:21:16,582
(英國皇家空軍戰鬥機飛行員 大衛·坎貝爾空軍中尉)

251
00:21:20,755 --> 00:21:22,450
來一杯,特德
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Pint of sludge, Ted.{\r}

252
00:21:30,900 --> 00:21:33,596
你好,戴夫,看到約翰尼沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, hello, Dave. Hey, you seen Johnny?{\r}

253
00:21:33,869 --> 00:21:35,063
有
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

254
00:21:35,805 --> 00:21:37,670
他在哪？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, where is he?{\r}

255
00:21:39,643 --> 00:21:41,099
說啊,戴夫
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on, Dave.{\r}

256
00:21:41,578 --> 00:21:43,910
他借走了我的靴子
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I need my boots. Johnny's borrowed them.{\r}

257
00:21:45,516 --> 00:21:47,143
他在哪？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Where is he?{\r}

258
00:21:47,785 --> 00:21:49,184
躺在……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}At the bottom...{\r}

259
00:21:49,420 --> 00:21:51,012
……海底
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...of the Channel.{\r}

260
00:22:00,166 --> 00:22:01,360
你是說……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You mean...{\r}

261
00:22:03,136 --> 00:22:04,364
……他死了？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...he's bought it?{\r}

262
00:22:04,604 --> 00:22:06,868
在加萊中了高射炮
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Ack-ack over Calais.{\r}

263
00:22:07,108 --> 00:22:11,101
他跳了出來,可降落傘沒能打開
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He jumped clean, ut his parachute didn't open.{\r}

264
00:22:19,821 --> 00:22:22,278
這個中隊只乘下你了,戴夫
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That leaves just you in the squadron, Dave.{\r}

265
00:22:23,493 --> 00:22:26,951
我是指一九四○年那一撥老兵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I mean, of the old 1940 mob.{\r}

266
00:22:27,163 --> 00:22:32,794
我們這批人越變越少，正是我一直擔心的事情之一
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What's always worried me about being one of the few...
...is the way we keep on getting fewer.{\r}

267
00:22:34,405 --> 00:22:35,667
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah.{\r}

268
00:22:36,173 --> 00:22:37,765
可憐的老約翰尼
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Poor old Johnny.{\r}

269
00:22:39,511 --> 00:22:40,773
運氣真糟,在這當口
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Bad luck, it happening now.{\r}

270
00:22:41,012 --> 00:22:45,437
－這當口？有什麼區別？
－他和你一樣捱過了不列顛戰役!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Now, then. What's the difference?
-He went through the Battle of Britain just like you!{\r}

271
00:22:47,219 --> 00:22:50,017
要是今晚好戲上場……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And now if the big show starts tonight...{\r}

272
00:22:50,222 --> 00:22:52,144
……他就不能加入
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...he won't be in it.{\r}

273
00:22:52,992 --> 00:22:55,085
請不要再提他好嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, will you please shut up about him?{\r}

274
00:22:55,362 --> 00:22:57,660
好的好的,對不起,對不起
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, all right. I'm sorry, I'm sorry.{\r}

275
00:22:58,365 --> 00:23:00,162
聽說今晚的事沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You heard something about tonight?{\r}

276
00:23:00,902 --> 00:23:03,325
不,沒有,什麼都沒聽到
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, no. I haven't heard anything.{\r}

277
00:23:03,571 --> 00:23:06,768
－那你剛才說的是什麼？
－這個,只是…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What are you talking about then?
-Well, it's just....{\r}

278
00:23:07,141 --> 00:23:10,474
－繼續,繼續
－我有種預感就是在今晚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Go on, go on.
-I have a feeling it's on for tonight.{\r}

279
00:23:10,746 --> 00:23:13,169
－如此而已
－預感
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-That's all.
-A feeling.{\r}

280
00:23:13,716 --> 00:23:15,672
帶著你的預感去別處吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Take your feeling somewhere else.{\r}

281
00:23:16,986 --> 00:23:18,613
我得寫封信
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've got a letter to write.{\r}

282
00:23:18,888 --> 00:23:21,516
我從早上起來時就有這種預感
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've had this feeling since I woke up.{\r}

283
00:23:21,991 --> 00:23:23,879
整天都有這種感覺
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've had it with me all day long.{\r}

284
00:23:24,562 --> 00:23:26,359
無法擺脫它
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't shake it off.{\r}

285
00:23:27,064 --> 00:23:30,227
就是今晚,我知道這一點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's tonight. I know it is.{\r}

286
00:23:30,534 --> 00:23:32,229
好吧,就是今晚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, it's tonight.{\r}

287
00:23:32,504 --> 00:23:33,801
正合我意
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Suits me fine.{\r}

288
00:23:34,039 --> 00:23:36,872
今晚,今天下午,現在!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Tonight. This afternoon. Now!{\r}

289
00:23:38,744 --> 00:23:40,268
我是說……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I mean...{\r}

290
00:23:41,914 --> 00:23:44,178
……在我喝完啤酒之後
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...as soon as I finish this beer.{\r}

291
00:23:58,400 --> 00:24:01,164
－將軍,你現在有空嗎？
－進來吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-General, can you spare me a minute?
-Come in.{\r}

292
00:24:01,403 --> 00:24:03,098
－謝謝
－要咖啡嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Thank you.
-Can I get you coffee?{\r}

293
00:24:03,406 --> 00:24:05,567
－不用,謝謝
－我可得來點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-No, thanks.
-I'll get some for myself.{\r}

294
00:24:05,775 --> 00:24:10,967
(美軍第八十二空降師副師長 詹姆斯·Ｍ·加文准將)

295
00:24:16,686 --> 00:24:17,812
還在下雨嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Is it still raining?{\r}

296
00:24:18,089 --> 00:24:19,613
下下停停,停停下下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}On and off, off and on.{\r}

297
00:24:19,924 --> 00:24:22,449
有時我想知道上帝究竟站在哪一邊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sometimes I wonder which side God's on.{\r}

298
00:24:22,693 --> 00:24:23,717
什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}

299
00:24:24,562 --> 00:24:28,350
我說,有時我想知道上帝站在哪一邊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I say, sometimes I wonder which side God's on.{\r}

300
00:24:28,934 --> 00:24:30,856
好問題
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Good question.{\r}

301
00:24:31,103 --> 00:24:32,593
你有何想法,范？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What's on your mind, Van?{\r}

302
00:24:32,805 --> 00:24:35,865
我擔心我們降落地點的安排
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm concerned about the placement of our drop zones.{\r}

303
00:24:36,109 --> 00:24:37,337
繼續說
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go on.{\r}

304
00:24:37,577 --> 00:24:41,138
我知道現在提出新方案太晚了點……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I know this is a hell of a late date
to bring up something new...{\r}

305
00:24:41,449 --> 00:24:43,679
……但你給我出了個難題
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...but you've given me a tough nut to crack.{\r}

306
00:24:43,951 --> 00:24:47,443
－我越想越覺得棘手
－我知道,范
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-It gets tougher every time I try.
-I know, Van.{\r}

307
00:24:47,655 --> 00:24:51,282
聖米爾伊格奡窗A座落在德軍唯一能用來……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sainte-Mere-Eglise straddles the only road
the Germans can use...{\r}

308
00:24:51,460 --> 00:24:54,918
……打入我軍北翼的公路上,我們必須拿下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...to drive into our northern flank. But it has to be taken.{\r}

309
00:24:55,330 --> 00:24:57,286
而且必須守住
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And it has to be held.{\r}

310
00:24:58,668 --> 00:25:01,125
所以我才要你去,范
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's why I gave you the job, Van.{\r}

311
00:25:04,808 --> 00:25:06,901
－能用下黑板嗎？
－當然
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Can I use your board?
-Of course.{\r}

312
00:25:11,816 --> 00:25:14,910
這是那個鎮,有重兵把守
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Here's the town. Heavily fortified.{\r}

313
00:25:15,153 --> 00:25:18,543
這是沼澤地,德軍已經引水淹沒
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Down here is the swamp area that
the Germans have flooded.{\r}

314
00:25:18,723 --> 00:25:22,511
這二者中間，距小鎮四英里處是我們的著陸點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And in between, four miles from the town, is our drop zone.{\r}

315
00:25:22,695 --> 00:25:25,323
如果出了差錯而提前著陸……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now, if anything goes wrong and we undershoot...{\r}

316
00:25:25,564 --> 00:25:28,419
……降落在沼澤地就會陷入困境
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...we land in this flooded area and are bogged down.{\r}

317
00:25:28,668 --> 00:25:31,899
如果飛過頭了,就會像泥鴿一樣落下……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If we overshoot, we come down like clay pigeons...{\r}

318
00:25:32,138 --> 00:25:35,062
……直接面對來自小鎮的火力
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...smack dab in the center of Sainte-Mere-Eglise.{\r}

319
00:25:35,276 --> 00:25:39,838
所以我在附近的村子訓練士兵低空跳傘
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's why I gave the men training
in low-level jumps near the villages.{\r}

320
00:25:40,047 --> 00:25:41,639
我聽說了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}So I've heard.{\r}

321
00:25:44,019 --> 00:25:47,546
我收到了來自貝克斯荷市議會的投訴
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Got a complaint from the city council at Bexhall.{\r}

322
00:25:47,756 --> 00:25:52,386
你的一些部下因飛過頭而降落在市區
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Some of your men overshot the drop zone
and landed in the town.{\r}

323
00:25:52,562 --> 00:25:56,384
－阻礙交通達一小時
－沒錯,頭,我也在那
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Tied up traffic for an hour.
-That's true, sir. I was with them.{\r}

324
00:25:56,699 --> 00:25:59,497
遭遇側風,將我們吹過了樹梢……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sudden crosswind hit us, swept us over the treetops...{\r}

325
00:25:59,737 --> 00:26:01,762
……大家都給吹散了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...scattered us all over the place.{\r}

326
00:26:03,541 --> 00:26:08,399
－你落在了哪？
－落在一家女修道院的院子
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Where did you end up?
-In the courtyard of a convent.{\r}

327
00:26:09,414 --> 00:26:11,405
放鬆點,范,坐吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Relax, Van. Sit down.{\r}

328
00:26:12,784 --> 00:26:16,743
幾個月來我們都吃盡了苦頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The last few months have been a tough grind on all of us.{\r}

329
00:26:17,390 --> 00:26:20,621
我聽說你和你的部下一直在刻苦訓練
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I hear you've been working yourself and your battalion hard.{\r}

330
00:26:20,827 --> 00:26:22,886
幾乎沒停過
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Almost without a stop.{\r}

331
00:26:24,431 --> 00:26:27,093
現在我們就要開始行動了……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now that we're almost at the end of the line...{\r}

332
00:26:27,301 --> 00:26:30,600
……你幹嘛不讓自己和部下放鬆一下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...why don't you try easing up on yourself and on the men?{\r}

333
00:26:31,139 --> 00:26:34,666
偶爾放鬆一下能讓部隊的狀態更好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sometimes a battalion can be sharpened to too fine a point.{\r}

334
00:26:35,076 --> 00:26:37,965
有時指揮官也一樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sometimes a commander can too.{\r}

335
00:26:40,416 --> 00:26:42,407
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well...{\r}

336
00:26:42,918 --> 00:26:46,445
如果行動繼續延後的話
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...if there's any further delay...{\r}

337
00:26:46,656 --> 00:26:50,422
……我請求允許重新安排降落地點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...I request permission to
submit a new placement for our drop zones.{\r}

338
00:26:50,660 --> 00:26:52,787
行,寫個報告吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right. Put it in writing.{\r}

339
00:26:53,097 --> 00:26:55,361
搞正式一點,這是你的職權
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Make it official. That's your prerogative.{\r}

340
00:26:56,133 --> 00:27:01,093
不過艾克今晚要在薩維克大樓召開一個決議會
(薩維克大樓——盟軍海軍司令部,位於樸次茅斯城外)
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But Ike has called a final meeting
for tonight at Southwick House.{\r}

341
00:27:01,607 --> 00:27:04,201
如果通過了,今晚九點三十就要出發
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If it's on, we'll get the green light by 9:30.{\r}

342
00:27:04,443 --> 00:27:07,207
－可能性有多大？
－超過五成
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What are the chances?
-Better than 50-50.{\r}

343
00:27:07,614 --> 00:27:11,436
當我什麼也沒說,將軍。我有這個師最好的一個營……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Forget everything I said.
I got the best battalion in this division...{\r}

344
00:27:11,618 --> 00:27:12,880
……而且已準備就緒
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and they're ready.{\r}

345
00:27:14,955 --> 00:27:19,881
(英國皇家空軍首席氣象顧問 Ｊ·Ｎ·斯塔格空軍上校)

346
00:27:28,670 --> 00:27:30,900
來了,最新的報告
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Here it is. The latest report.{\r}

347
00:27:49,661 --> 00:27:52,516
－薩維克大樓(盟軍海軍司令部)打來的,長官
－我是斯塔格
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-It's Southwick House, sir.
-Stagg here.{\r}

348
00:27:52,997 --> 00:27:56,558
是的,長官,新鋒的移動比預期的要快
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir. The new front's moving
in much faster than we thought.{\r}

349
00:27:57,536 --> 00:27:59,902
是的,很明顯有所改善
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir, it's definitely improving.{\r}

350
00:28:01,508 --> 00:28:03,703
我會到的,長官,九點三十
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll be there, sir. 9:30.{\r}

351
00:28:10,217 --> 00:28:13,880
－還要茶嗎,長官？
－咖啡吧,濃一點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Would you like some more tea, sir?
-Coffee, and make it black.{\r}

352
00:28:14,088 --> 00:28:15,146
謝謝
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Please.{\r}

353
00:28:15,589 --> 00:28:17,454
等等,普堸リ亢
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}One moment, Colonel Priller.{\r}

354
00:28:18,226 --> 00:28:20,353
他為什麼沒受軍法處治？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Why wasn't he court-martialed?{\r}

355
00:28:20,562 --> 00:28:22,518
他打下了一百三十二架飛機
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He shot down 132 planes.{\r}

356
00:28:22,698 --> 00:28:26,291
(德國空軍西線總部 沃爾夫岡·海格空軍中將)

357
00:28:24,267 --> 00:28:26,292
你好,「匹普斯」老夥計
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello, Pips, old boy.{\r}

358
00:28:26,515 --> 00:28:32,460
(德國空軍第二十六戰鬥機聯隊聯隊長約瑟夫·普堸リ亢)
(共擊落一百零一架飛機,其中四引擎轟炸機十一架)
別叫我「匹普斯」老夥計
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't call me "Pips, old boy."{\r}

359
00:28:29,739 --> 00:28:33,129
我們在蘇聯時你就是個糟糕的飛行員
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You were a rotten pilot when we flew in Russia.{\r}

360
00:28:33,377 --> 00:28:36,904
你現在陞官了,可仍然是糟糕的飛行員
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You're flying a desk now, but you're still a rotten pilot!{\r}

361
00:28:37,848 --> 00:28:40,180
你這是什麼話？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What's that you're saying?{\r}

362
00:28:40,385 --> 00:28:44,674
我窩在這樣一個見鬼的機場……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm squatting here on this God-forsaken airfield...{\r}

363
00:28:44,923 --> 00:28:49,383
……就兩架飛機,純粹是兩堆破爛
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...with only two planes, two stinking crates!{\r}

364
00:28:51,097 --> 00:28:54,430
當然,你的命令倒是生效了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, sure, sure, your orders were followed!{\r}

365
00:28:54,633 --> 00:28:56,931
可我的中隊天知道在哪!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now my squadrons are God-knows-where!{\r}

366
00:28:57,437 --> 00:29:02,568
給養早就沒了,我現在該做什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}My supplies are all gone. What am I supposed to do now?{\r}

367
00:29:02,777 --> 00:29:07,976
但是「匹普斯」,我們必須分散飛行中隊,必須!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But Pips, we had to disperse our fighter squadrons. We had to!{\r}

368
00:29:08,182 --> 00:29:12,505
看看我們加萊附近的機場遭受了什麼!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Look what happened to our airstrips around the Pas-de-Calais!{\r}

369
00:29:12,721 --> 00:29:15,554
這種主意真是愚蠢之極!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The whole idea is absolutely idiotic!{\r}

370
00:29:15,958 --> 00:29:19,951
你不讓我們前進反而讓我們後退
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You move us back instead of forward!{\r}

371
00:29:20,196 --> 00:29:25,122
當然,我知道天氣惡劣,所以他們不一定會進攻……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sure, I know the weather's lousy
and they probably won't invade...{\r}

372
00:29:25,335 --> 00:29:28,463
……但萬一他們進攻該怎麼辦？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...but what would happen if they did?{\r}

373
00:29:28,706 --> 00:29:32,836
你該瞭解以我的裝備至少要兩天才能趕到
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But you know I can't get there with my equipment for two days.{\r}

374
00:29:33,110 --> 00:29:36,705
老實說,你們全都瘋了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I tell you, you're all crazy!{\r}

375
00:29:54,835 --> 00:29:57,326
普堸Щ`是這麼急躁……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Priller has always been a hothead...{\r}

376
00:29:57,639 --> 00:30:00,335
……但不要因此而輕視他
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...but let's not underestimate him.{\r}

377
00:30:01,242 --> 00:30:04,075
他的話不無道理
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What he says is not entirely illogical.{\r}

378
00:30:05,147 --> 00:30:06,842
天氣報告怎麼說？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What's the weather report?{\r}

379
00:30:07,149 --> 00:30:09,379
整個海峽稍有好轉
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Slightly better over the Channel.{\r}

380
00:30:10,319 --> 00:30:12,549
我想不會有意外,即使……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I wouldn't be surprised if--{\r}

381
00:30:14,324 --> 00:30:18,146
－下次天氣報告什麼時候到？
－今晚八點,將軍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-When's the next weather report?
-Tonight at 8, general.{\r}

382
00:30:19,162 --> 00:30:21,619
隨時向我報告天氣情況
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Keep me posted on the weather.{\r}

383
00:30:22,667 --> 00:30:24,726
替我訂好晚餐座位沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You made my dinner reservations?{\r}

384
00:30:25,002 --> 00:30:26,731
訂好了,將軍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, I did, general.{\r}

385
00:30:27,005 --> 00:30:28,632
全部取消
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Cancel everything.{\r}

386
00:30:39,719 --> 00:30:41,380
－拿了沒有？
－拿了,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Have you got them?
-Yes, sir.{\r}

387
00:30:41,554 --> 00:30:42,646
給我
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me have them.{\r}

388
00:30:42,890 --> 00:30:48,487
是送給我太太的鞋,特地在巴黎訂做的……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Shoes for my wife, I had them specially made in Paris...{\r}

389
00:30:48,762 --> 00:30:53,586
……為她慶祝生日,就是明天,六月六號
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...for her birthday, tomorrow, the sixth of June.{\r}

390
00:30:53,768 --> 00:30:56,191
代我祝她生日快樂
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Please wish her a happy birthday.{\r}

391
00:30:56,404 --> 00:30:57,860
謝謝,斯派達爾
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you, Speidel.{\r}

392
00:31:01,043 --> 00:31:04,467
他們幹嘛不在五月進攻？ 那麼理想的天氣……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Why didn't they attack in May? The weather was perfect....{\r}

393
00:31:04,680 --> 00:31:08,070
潮汐都很正常,可現在…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Tides were right, and now....{\r}

394
00:31:08,418 --> 00:31:10,511
現在進攻就變得艱難了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}An attack now would be embarrassing.{\r}

395
00:31:10,687 --> 00:31:15,010
開車, 但我們用不著擔心
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's go. But I don't think we need worry.{\r}

396
00:31:15,688 --> 00:31:18,011
(德軍西線Ｂ集團軍群參謀長 漢斯·斯派達爾博士少將)
(積極參與推翻希特勒密謀活動並牽連到隆美爾)
(戰後,於1957年出任北約地面部隊總司令)

397
00:31:30,543 --> 00:31:34,501
(德軍第七集團軍第八十四軍軍長 埃堜_·馬克斯中將)

398
00:31:37,485 --> 00:31:39,043
計劃準備好了嗎,長官？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Is the plan ready, sir?{\r}

399
00:31:39,553 --> 00:31:42,909
是的,計劃好了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, yes, quite finished.{\r}

400
00:31:44,559 --> 00:31:46,083
戰棋推演……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}War games...{\r}

401
00:31:47,629 --> 00:31:49,961
……理論性的入侵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...theoretical invasions.{\r}

402
00:31:50,999 --> 00:31:56,960
趕去雷恩只是為了在沙盤上插些小旗罷了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Rush to Rennes just to push little flags around a table.{\r}

403
00:31:59,843 --> 00:32:01,834
戰爭中的遊戲!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Playing at war!{\r}

404
00:32:04,081 --> 00:32:06,276
您是贏是輸,長官？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you win or lose, sir?{\r}

405
00:32:07,652 --> 00:32:09,108
我輸過嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Have I ever lost?{\r}

406
00:32:12,991 --> 00:32:17,883
但是將軍,這次您扮演的是艾森豪威爾
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But general, this time you play the role of Eisenhower.{\r}

407
00:32:18,597 --> 00:32:21,896
我贏是因為我不會依常規行事
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I win because I go against the rules.{\r}

408
00:32:23,036 --> 00:32:26,699
預料中敵人將從海峽最窄之處渡海……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We expect them
to cross at the narrowest part of the Channel...{\r}

409
00:32:27,007 --> 00:32:31,797
……而且是在好天氣,但過於顯而易見
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and in good weather. But that's too simple, too obvious.{\r}

410
00:32:32,013 --> 00:32:37,110
我選的是最寬之處,在最惡劣的天氣,進攻此地
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I choose the widest part, in the worst weather,
and attack here.{\r}

411
00:32:38,220 --> 00:32:39,676
諾曼底
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In Normandy.{\r}

412
00:32:40,122 --> 00:32:41,714
在惡劣天氣之中
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And in bad weather!{\r}

413
00:32:46,062 --> 00:32:47,324
例如現在……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Like now...{\r}

414
00:32:48,131 --> 00:32:49,291
……這種壞天氣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...bad weather!{\r}

415
00:32:49,766 --> 00:32:52,929
要作出判斷很困難
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Trying to pick a trend is difficult.{\r}

416
00:32:53,704 --> 00:32:58,368
從氣象角度來說,目前的情形簡直像是寒冬
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}From a meteorological standpoint,
conditions almost resemble mid-winter.{\r}

417
00:32:58,576 --> 00:32:59,770
至於諾曼底
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And Normandy?{\r}

418
00:33:00,011 --> 00:33:03,572
強風,雲層,以及霧氣籠罩著整個海灘
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}High winds, clouds, and some fog over the beaches.{\r}

419
00:33:03,882 --> 00:33:07,909
不管怎樣,我能完全肯定的是……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}However, I can say with a certain degree of safety...{\r}

420
00:33:08,153 --> 00:33:11,384
……將有一段短時間的好天氣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...that we can expect a brief period of fair conditions.{\r}

421
00:33:11,657 --> 00:33:13,613
那麼換而言之
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let me summarize, then.{\r}

422
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:19,018
你能保證的就是將有一段極為短暫的好天氣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What you're promising us is
a barely tolerable period of fair conditions.{\r}

423
00:33:19,400 --> 00:33:20,355
是不是這樣？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Am I right?{\r}

424
00:33:20,567 --> 00:33:21,693
是的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

425
00:33:21,902 --> 00:33:25,531
這樣的條件遠遠低於最低要求
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Conditions that are far below the minimum requirements.{\r}

426
00:33:25,740 --> 00:33:28,163
