{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, there it is.{\r}

429
00:33:40,290 --> 00:33:43,282
我們已將進攻推遲過一次
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We've postponed the attack once already.{\r}

430
00:33:43,927 --> 00:33:47,954
現在,要麼趁六號的最低條件發動進攻……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now, either we go on the sixth,
with only marginal conditions...{\r}

431
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:50,763
……要麼再次延後……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...or postpone again...{\r}

432
00:33:51,235 --> 00:33:53,692
……等待理想的氣候條件
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...in the hope of getting perfect conditions.{\r}

433
00:33:53,938 --> 00:33:55,599
你覺得怎樣,蒙蒂？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you think, Monty?{\r}

434
00:33:55,808 --> 00:33:57,901
我選擇進攻,進攻
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I say, go. Go.{\r}

435
00:33:58,110 --> 00:34:00,408
我必須提醒各位……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I must remind everybody...{\r}

436
00:34:00,612 --> 00:34:04,503
……負責進攻「奧馬哈海灘」和「猶他海灘」的美軍船隊……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...that the American convoy for the Omaha and Utah beaches...{\r}

437
00:34:04,751 --> 00:34:06,616
……行程最遠……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...they've farthest to go...{\r}

438
00:34:06,820 --> 00:34:10,119
……必須在半小時以內向他們下令……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...must be given the order within the next half-hour...{\r}

439
00:34:10,324 --> 00:34:13,487
……如果突襲安排在六號的話
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...if the assault is to take place on the sixth.{\r}

440
00:34:17,064 --> 00:34:20,625
我們不能讓將近二十五萬人一直呆在船上……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We can't keep almost a quarter of a million men on ships...{\r}

441
00:34:20,969 --> 00:34:23,824
