好了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Clear.{\r}

650
00:55:44,051 --> 00:55:45,780
成功了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's working!{\r}

651
00:55:46,387 --> 00:55:48,912
喂!喂!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello! Hello!{\r}

652
00:55:52,727 --> 00:55:54,786
－醫生在哪？
－第三架滑翔機上
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Where's the doc?
-On the third glider.{\r}

653
00:55:54,963 --> 00:55:56,692
沒收到他們的報告
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There's no report from them.{\r}

654
00:55:56,898 --> 00:55:58,786
－沃爾什
－頭？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Walsh.
-Sir?{\r}

655
00:55:59,068 --> 00:56:01,696
湯姆他們已經得手了,你去接管
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Tom, Ruskin and Royal have had it. Take over.{\r}

656
00:56:01,938 --> 00:56:03,769
在橋的另一頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}On the other end of the bridge.{\r}

657
00:56:03,973 --> 00:56:06,339
－你怎麼了？
－著陸時弄斷了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What happened to you?
-Broke it on landing.{\r}

658
00:56:06,577 --> 00:56:08,909
－醫生沒和你們在一起？
－他失蹤了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Isn't the doc with you?
-No, he's missing.{\r}

659
00:56:09,112 --> 00:56:12,502
我們落在了河,只怕傷亡慘重
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We crashed in the river. Afraid we've got a lot of casualties.{\r}

660
00:56:13,216 --> 00:56:15,138
我沒事,頭,弟兄們一樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm all right, sir. So are the boys.{\r}

661
00:56:15,420 --> 00:56:18,719
－好,繼續行動
－好的,頭,跟我來!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Okay, carry on.
-Right, sir. Come on!{\r}

662
00:56:41,949 --> 00:56:43,473
我真要…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, I'll be....{\r}

663
00:56:44,051 --> 00:56:45,609
嘿,醫生,醫生
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, doc! Doc!{\r}

664
00:56:46,655 --> 00:56:48,987
你在那幹嘛？那邊是德國人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing there? That's the German side.{\r}

665
00:56:49,191 --> 00:56:52,149
長官,誰都可能犯錯
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sir, anybody can make a mistake.{\r}

666
00:57:02,973 --> 00:57:03,997
頭？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sir?{\r}

667
00:57:04,241 --> 00:57:07,438
爆破裝置已拆除,徹底安全了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The demolition charges have been removed. It's all clear.{\r}

668
00:57:07,679 --> 00:57:09,442
很好,史密斯下士
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Good. Corporal Smith.{\r}

669
00:57:11,216 --> 00:57:15,038
發送成功信號,直到收到確認信號
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Send out the success code words.
Keep sending until acknowledged.{\r}

670
00:57:16,489 --> 00:57:20,152
－約翰,在碉堡設立指揮部
－好的,頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-John, set up HQ in that pillbox.
-Right, sir.{\r}

671
00:57:24,798 --> 00:57:27,323
不到十五分鐘就搞定了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All in less than 15 minutes.{\r}

672
00:57:30,638 --> 00:57:32,902
他們的反攻只是時間問題
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Only a matter of time before they counterattack.{\r}

673
00:57:33,074 --> 00:57:37,170
－傘兵呢？
－第七傘兵營恐怕要數小時後才到
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What about the paratroopers?
-7th Para might not get here for hours.{\r}

674
00:57:37,545 --> 00:57:39,638
拉瓦特和他的突擊隊…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And Lovat and his commandos....{\r}

675
00:57:40,549 --> 00:57:42,938
可能要午後才能到
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It could be midday before they get here.{\r}

676
00:57:44,319 --> 00:57:46,708
問題就是我們能守多久了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The question is, how long can we hold?{\r}

677
00:57:47,590 --> 00:57:49,319
守至援軍到來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold until relieved.{\r}

678
00:57:50,360 --> 00:57:52,191
守至援軍到來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold until relieved.{\r}

679
00:57:58,335 --> 00:58:02,299
(德軍第七集團軍參謀長 麥克斯·彭塞爾少將)
(德軍第七集團軍指揮部)

680
00:58:00,271 --> 00:58:04,401
天氣真糟,又下雨了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What awful weather. It's raining again.{\r}

681
00:58:04,910 --> 00:58:06,104
謝謝
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you.{\r}

682
00:58:06,745 --> 00:58:08,406
拿到名單了嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you get the list?{\r}

683
00:58:12,652 --> 00:58:17,544
七○九師師長卡爾·馮·施萊本中將已前往參加戰棋推演
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}General Schlieben of the 709th
has already left for the war games.{\r}

684
00:58:18,225 --> 00:58:23,857
二四三師師長海因茨·赫爾密奇中將也於晚上六點去了雷恩
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The commander of the 243rd left for Rennes at 1800 hours.{\r}

685
00:58:24,064 --> 00:58:25,053
還有呢？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Who else?{\r}

686
00:58:25,233 --> 00:58:28,760
還有三五二師的齊默曼,總共十二名軍官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Also, Zimmermann of the 352nd, 12 officers in all.{\r}

687
00:58:29,904 --> 00:58:31,895
是啊,我知道
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, I know.{\r}

688
00:58:32,675 --> 00:58:36,964
天氣不好,所以全都想在雷恩多享受一晚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The weather is bad,
so everyone enjoys an extra night in Rennes.{\r}

689
00:58:38,214 --> 00:58:39,772
我不喜歡這樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't like it.{\r}

690
00:58:40,083 --> 00:58:41,380
一點都不
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Any of it.{\r}

691
00:58:41,585 --> 00:58:44,782
這麼多重要軍官同時不在
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}So many key officers are away at the same time.{\r}

692
00:58:45,088 --> 00:58:47,147
不知道為什麼,但我就是不喜歡
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know why, but I don't like it.{\r}

693
00:58:48,192 --> 00:58:51,525
但戰棋推演一周前就定好了日期……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But the war games have been scheduled for a week....{\r}

694
00:58:51,763 --> 00:58:55,529
對,是明天,不是今晚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, for tomorrow, not tonight.{\r}

695
00:58:57,936 --> 00:59:01,599
建議所有尚未前往雷恩的軍官……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Advise all officers who have not yet left for Rennes...{\r}

696
00:59:01,807 --> 00:59:04,799
……推遲行程，到明天再說
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...to postpone their departure until tomorrow.{\r}

697
00:59:05,111 --> 00:59:07,841
容我提醒您,將軍……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}May I remind you, general...{\r}

698
00:59:08,114 --> 00:59:11,811
……盟軍向來是在理想的天氣條件下才登陸
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...that the Allies have always landed
in perfect weather conditions.{\r}

699
00:59:11,986 --> 00:59:16,082
北非,西西里,意大利…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}North Africa, Sicily, ltaly....{\r}

700
00:59:16,824 --> 00:59:18,314
對,總是在黎明時分
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, and always at dawn.{\r}

701
00:59:27,003 --> 00:59:29,801
我們還有十一分鐘就要跳傘
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're 11 minutes from the green light.{\r}

702
00:59:30,006 --> 00:59:32,201
現在,我再重複一次
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now, once more, I repeat:{\r}

703
00:59:32,742 --> 00:59:36,200
如果意外降落到錯誤的地點……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If, for any reason, we fail to hit our drop zones...{\r}

704
00:59:36,480 --> 00:59:38,311
……就朝東北方向前進
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...move north by east.{\r}

705
00:59:38,682 --> 00:59:40,445
東北方向
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}North by east.{\r}

706
00:59:40,951 --> 00:59:44,478
德軍已經淹沒了海岸後方的大面積沼澤地
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Germans have flooded large swamp areas behind the coast.{\r}

707
00:59:44,689 --> 00:59:46,850
盡量避開那
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Avoid them if possible.{\r}

708
00:59:47,158 --> 00:59:49,956
我們是來打仗,不是來游泳
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We came here to fight, not to swim.{\r}

709
00:59:50,362 --> 00:59:51,795
聽清楚沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you read me?{\r}

710
00:59:51,964 --> 00:59:53,295
聽清楚了,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Loud and clear, sir.{\r}

711
01:00:15,257 --> 01:00:16,884
結果如何？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How'd you make out?{\r}

712
01:00:17,893 --> 01:00:19,758
你加入賭局的結果如何？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How did you make out at the game?{\r}

713
01:00:21,698 --> 01:00:23,996
輸了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I lost.{\r}

714
01:00:26,202 --> 01:00:28,500
現在我們都能安全著陸了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now we're both jumping clean.{\r}

715
01:00:46,225 --> 01:00:49,956
我明白,元帥將於何時返回？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I understand. And when will the field marshal return?{\r}

716
01:00:51,899 --> 01:00:53,696
知道了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I see. Oh, well.{\r}

717
01:00:53,901 --> 01:00:55,300
等一下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Just a moment.{\r}

718
01:00:57,070 --> 01:00:58,697
雷達報告
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The radar report.{\r}

719
01:01:02,243 --> 01:01:05,701
我們收到報告說雷達受到強烈干擾……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We are getting reports of strong radar interference...{\r}

720
01:01:06,248 --> 01:01:08,580
……無線電接收也有阻礙
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and radio reception is jammed.{\r}

721
01:01:10,753 --> 01:01:15,076
我知道以前也有過,但從未如此嚴重
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I realize this has happened before,
but never this effectively!{\r}

722
01:01:15,258 --> 01:01:17,055
而且……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And the--{\r}

723
01:01:17,761 --> 01:01:20,594
打給西線統帥部？好吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Call the OB West? Very well.{\r}

724
01:01:21,131 --> 01:01:24,692
元帥返回後代我問候他
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Give my respects to the field marshal when he returns.{\r}

725
01:01:27,305 --> 01:01:31,865
(卡昂,凌晨一時○七分)

726
01:01:57,839 --> 01:02:02,264
再見,魯珀特,為上帝,國王,和你的國家效力吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Bye, Rupert. Do your duty for God, king, and your country.{\r}

727
01:03:06,183 --> 01:03:09,346
請求增援!我們遭到攻擊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Call for reinforcements! We're under attack!{\r}

728
01:03:10,722 --> 01:03:14,681
往前走!上火車!快!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Forward! Board! Fast!{\r}

729
01:04:32,580 --> 01:04:34,571
－我們來晚了嗎？
－不,不過……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Are we late?
-No, but...{\r}

730
01:04:34,817 --> 01:04:36,341
……我們得趕快!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...we must hurry!{\r}

731
01:05:48,266 --> 01:05:49,460
怎麼了？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What is it?{\r}

732
01:05:56,775 --> 01:05:58,333
我去
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll go.{\r}

733
01:06:18,133 --> 01:06:19,191
站住!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop!{\r}

734
01:06:20,435 --> 01:06:21,595
我說站住!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We said, stop!{\r}

735
01:06:22,005 --> 01:06:23,996
站住,不然開槍了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop, or I'll shoot!{\r}

736
01:06:28,878 --> 01:06:30,106
你在這幹什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What are you doing here?{\r}

737
01:06:30,914 --> 01:06:33,007
我住在那個村子
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I live in that farm.{\r}

738
01:06:33,684 --> 01:06:36,642
那個村子沒人住
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nobody lives in that farm.{\r}

739
01:06:37,922 --> 01:06:40,618
－是空的
－出示你的證件
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-It's abandoned.
-Show me your papers.{\r}

740
01:06:42,160 --> 01:06:43,616
快點!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hurry up!{\r}

741
01:06:48,801 --> 01:06:50,462
跟我走
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come with me.{\r}

742
01:06:50,936 --> 01:06:52,130
快點!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go on!{\r}

743
01:07:31,717 --> 01:07:33,708
把腳踏車放在那
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Put your bicycle there.{\r}

744
01:07:34,653 --> 01:07:35,847
漢斯!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hans!{\r}

745
01:07:37,055 --> 01:07:38,818
漢斯,你在哪？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hans, where are you?{\r}

746
01:07:40,193 --> 01:07:43,321
－是怎麼回事？
－沒什麼事!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What's going on here?
-Nothing!{\r}

747
01:07:43,930 --> 01:07:46,353
有誰和你一起？快說!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Who is with you? I want to know!{\r}

748
01:07:55,710 --> 01:07:57,007
停下!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop!{\r}

749
01:07:57,445 --> 01:07:58,742
停下!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop!{\r}

750
01:08:11,595 --> 01:08:12,857
停下!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop!{\r}

751
01:08:17,668 --> 01:08:20,592
停下!停下!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stop! Stop!{\r}

752
01:09:09,159 --> 01:09:11,457
祝你在戰棋推演中取勝,將軍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Good luck at the war games, general.{\r}

753
01:09:14,165 --> 01:09:15,928
有重要消息嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Anything important?{\r}

754
01:09:16,167 --> 01:09:19,989
通信兵報告說很難和前方取得聯繫
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Communications reports difficulty
in contacting our forward posts.{\r}

755
01:09:21,373 --> 01:09:23,329
又是地下組織!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Underground again!{\r}

756
01:09:24,176 --> 01:09:28,601
有一些用降落傘空降的橡膠假人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Some sort of rubber dummies have been dropped by parachute.{\r}

757
01:09:29,216 --> 01:09:30,672
橡膠假人!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Rubber dummies!{\r}

758
01:09:32,552 --> 01:09:34,474
給我接塈J特將軍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Connect me with General Richter!{\r}

759
01:09:34,689 --> 01:09:39,717
我們早料到將會有突襲
和其他牽制性行動……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We can expect commando raids and other diversionary tactics...{\r}

760
01:09:41,697 --> 01:09:45,224
……但我不喜歡假人傘兵這種主意
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...but I don't like this idea of dummy parachutists.{\r}

761
01:09:46,201 --> 01:09:49,967
我是馬克斯,對
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Marcks speaking. Yes.{\r}

762
01:09:51,341 --> 01:09:53,832
你肯定？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you certain?{\r}

763
01:09:54,010 --> 01:09:55,466
有多少？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How many?{\r}

764
01:09:57,047 --> 01:09:58,639
你有什麼看法？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you think of it?{\r}

765
01:10:00,017 --> 01:10:02,713
謝謝,塈J特
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you, Richter.{\r}

766
01:10:03,287 --> 01:10:08,145
報告說發現傘兵,這,這,還有這
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Paratroopers reported here, here and here!{\r}

767
01:10:11,263 --> 01:10:12,696
放在那
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Put it over there.{\r}

768
01:10:19,739 --> 01:10:23,402
這就是空降的假人,碰到地面就會爆炸
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}This is what they dropped,
they explode on contact with the earth.{\r}

769
01:10:23,744 --> 01:10:26,167
在黑暗中看起來就像士兵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In the dark, they look like soldiers.{\r}

770
01:10:26,446 --> 01:10:31,645
也許塈J特將軍看到的就是這個,而不是真的傘兵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Perhaps these are what General Richter saw,
not real paratroopers.{\r}

771
01:10:40,763 --> 01:10:45,894
當你組織一次佯攻時,總會有某種目的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}When you create a diversion, it's for a reason.{\r}

772
01:10:46,102 --> 01:10:48,900
替我接彭塞爾將軍!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Connect me with General Pemsel!{\r}

773
01:10:53,277 --> 01:10:54,403
假人……？!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Dummies...?!{\r}

774
01:10:54,912 --> 01:10:56,539
橡膠假人!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Rubber dummies!{\r}

775
01:10:58,450 --> 01:11:03,410
我同意你的看法,將軍,我會再打給你
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I agree with you, general.
I'll call you back.{\r}

776
01:11:05,791 --> 01:11:07,656
接通馮·龍德施泰特沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What about my call to von Rundstedt?{\r}

777
01:11:07,860 --> 01:11:10,624
無法取得聯絡,主幹線似乎被切斷了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We haven't been able to reach him.
The main lines seem to be cut.{\r}

778
01:11:10,797 --> 01:11:13,220
正在嘗試其他聯絡方式
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Colonel Helmdach is trying to re-route the call.{\r}

779
01:11:15,302 --> 01:11:17,133
他們投下假人……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They wouldn't drop dummies...{\r}

780
01:11:17,304 --> 01:11:20,228
……肯定是想轉移我們的注意力
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...unless it was to divert our attention from something else.{\r}

781
01:11:20,441 --> 01:11:21,931
在這種天氣？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In this weather?{\r}

782
01:11:22,143 --> 01:11:23,735
什麼天氣都一樣!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In any kind of weather!{\r}

783
01:11:23,979 --> 01:11:26,937
我必須聯絡西線統帥部
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I must get in touch with OB West.{\r}

784
01:12:21,009 --> 01:12:24,103
他們是敵人的傘兵!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They're enemy paratroopers!{\r}

785
01:12:38,328 --> 01:12:40,216
見鬼,夥計……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Blimey, mate...{\r}

786
01:12:40,532 --> 01:12:43,524
……你們會吵醒所有可惡的德國兵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...you'll wake up the whole blooming German Army!{\r}

787
01:13:20,577 --> 01:13:21,805
夥計們!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fellas!{\r}

788
01:13:22,078 --> 01:13:23,773
我被掛住了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm hung up!{\r}

789
01:13:24,414 --> 01:13:25,506
夥計們!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fellas!{\r}

790
01:13:37,095 --> 01:13:39,393
－你沒事吧？
－沒事
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Are you all right?
-Yeah.{\r}

791
01:15:17,742 --> 01:15:19,539
你們是從哪來的？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Where have you come from?{\r}

792
01:15:21,714 --> 01:15:23,409
非常抱歉,老頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Awfully sorry, old man.{\r}

793
01:15:23,716 --> 01:15:25,843
我們在這兒著陸的只能算是陰錯陽差
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Simply landed here by accident.{\r}

794
01:15:32,425 --> 01:15:33,881
是誰？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What's that?{\r}

795
01:15:34,761 --> 01:15:37,753
抱歉嚇到你了,我在找我的聖餐餐具
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sorry I startled you. I'm trying to find my communion set.{\r}

796
01:15:37,965 --> 01:15:41,389
－你的什麼？
－聖餐餐具,我把它弄丟了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Your what?
-My communion set. I've lost it.{\r}

797
01:15:41,736 --> 01:15:44,534
聽著神父,我們沒時間來找……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now listen, padre. We've got no time to look for--{\r}

798
01:15:51,080 --> 01:15:53,446
我肯定是在這弄丟的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sure that it was here that I lost it.{\r}

799
01:16:13,271 --> 01:16:16,763
我們處在火力之中,神父,你不覺得應該……？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're under fire, padre. Don't you think we ought to--?{\r}

800
01:16:16,976 --> 01:16:20,639
你走吧,我的孩子,走,我很快就能找到
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You go on, my boy. Go on. I'm sure I shall only be a minute.{\r}

801
01:16:22,783 --> 01:16:24,978
老天!真是沒辦法
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Cor! Stuff a grouse.{\r}

802
01:16:29,424 --> 01:16:31,255
我找到了!我找到了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've got it! I've got it!{\r}

803
01:16:31,492 --> 01:16:33,255
太好了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Glory be.{\r}

804
01:16:33,494 --> 01:16:37,282
現在,我的孩子,我們去完成上帝的使命
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now, my son, let's go about God's work this night.{\r}

805
01:16:49,546 --> 01:16:51,844
我是普拉斯凱
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Pluskat.{\r}

806
01:16:52,845 --> 01:16:54,819
(奧克中校)
(德軍第三五二海防師)

807
01:16:54,819 --> 01:16:57,117
喂,普拉斯凱,能聽到嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello, Pluskat! Do you hear me?{\r}

808
01:17:00,826 --> 01:17:02,350
我什麼都沒聽到…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing that I've heard....{\r}

809
01:17:04,629 --> 01:17:08,326
是經常有的爆炸聲,但相當遠
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The usual bombing, but quite distant.{\r}

810
01:17:10,503 --> 01:17:12,767
是的,我聽到了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, yes, I can hear it.{\r}

811
01:17:14,340 --> 01:17:15,739
等一下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, wait a minute.{\r}

812
01:17:16,010 --> 01:17:17,875
是的,稍等一下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, just a moment.{\r}

813
01:17:31,694 --> 01:17:35,983
有閃光,但離海岸很遠
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Flares, but a long way up the coast.{\r}

814
01:17:36,532 --> 01:17:39,558
是的,瑟堡又遭到了攻擊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, Cherbourg is getting hit again.{\r}

815
01:17:40,037 --> 01:17:42,631
也許沒什麼事……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There's probably nothing to it...{\r}

816
01:17:43,440 --> 01:17:47,900
……但是收到報告說有傘兵降落
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...but we have had reports of paratrooper landings.{\r}

817
01:17:48,179 --> 01:17:51,171
我去工事上看看
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll go to my bunker and take a look.{\r}

818
01:17:51,749 --> 01:17:53,614
謝謝,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you, sir.{\r}

819
01:17:56,021 --> 01:18:02,745
(聖米爾伊格奡,凌晨二時○三分)

820
01:18:11,939 --> 01:18:14,169
高一點!高一點!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Higher! Higher!{\r}

821
01:18:18,513 --> 01:18:22,335
路易斯,打開你的店門,我們還要些桶子
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Louis, open your store. We need more buckets!{\r}

822
01:18:27,590 --> 01:18:30,252
雷諾鎮長,你得馬上跟我來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Mayor Renaud, you must come with me immediately.{\r}

823
01:18:30,460 --> 01:18:33,850
－有要緊事嗎？
－非常要緊,雷諾鎮長
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Is it important?
-Very important, Mayor Renaud.{\r}

824
01:18:43,942 --> 01:18:45,466
怎麼了,夫人？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What's wrong, madam?{\r}

825
01:18:45,643 --> 01:18:47,235
我在去外邊小屋的路上…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I was on my way to the little house outside....{\r}

826
01:18:47,545 --> 01:18:48,910
好的,繼續說
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, yes, go on.{\r}

827
01:18:49,181 --> 01:18:52,036
突然看到有個人從天而降
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Suddenly, I saw a man fall from the sky.{\r}

828
01:18:52,318 --> 01:18:54,183
－傘兵？
－是的,一點沒錯
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-A parachutist?
-Yes, that's right.{\r}

829
01:18:54,453 --> 01:18:56,011
看起來就像只白色大鳥
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He looked like a big white bird!{\r}

830
01:18:56,256 --> 01:18:58,349
－英國人還是德國人？
－什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-British or German?
-What?{\r}

831
01:18:58,625 --> 01:19:00,957
那個傘兵是朋友還是敵人？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The parachutist, was he a friend or an enemy?{\r}

832
01:19:01,194 --> 01:19:04,823
我不知道,他只說「噓」,然後就不見了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know. He disappeared without a word. Just "Shh!"{\r}

833
01:19:05,166 --> 01:19:07,361
－什麼都沒說
－只說「噓」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Without a word?
-Just "Shh!"{\r}

834
01:19:15,544 --> 01:19:17,239
(法語)早,女士
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Bonjour, madame...{\r}

835
01:19:17,646 --> 01:19:19,534
(法語)我是美國人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...je suis americain.{\r}

836
01:19:20,116 --> 01:19:22,072
(法語)早,小姐
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Bonjour, mademoiselle...{\r}

837
01:19:22,685 --> 01:19:24,084
(法語)我是美國人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...je suis americain.{\r}

838
01:19:26,490 --> 01:19:28,321
我們似乎在兜圈子
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We seem to be circling.{\r}

839
01:19:29,059 --> 01:19:32,324
沒準他們找不到降落地點了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Maybe they're having difficulty finding the drop zone.{\r}

840
01:19:33,497 --> 01:19:34,828
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Je suis...{\r}

841
01:19:35,066 --> 01:19:36,431
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...amercan.{\r}

842
01:19:36,668 --> 01:19:39,228
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Je suis amricain.{\r}

843
01:19:40,372 --> 01:19:41,862
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Voulez-vous...{\r}

844
01:19:42,041 --> 01:19:43,167
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...mademoiselle?{\r}

845
01:19:45,011 --> 01:19:47,036
好了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay.{\r}

846
01:19:47,213 --> 01:19:48,544
跳!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go!{\r}

847
01:19:49,316 --> 01:19:50,578
跳!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go!{\r}

848
01:19:51,785 --> 01:19:54,982
跳!跳!跳!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go! Go! Go!{\r}

849
01:20:23,621 --> 01:20:25,316
傘兵!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Paratroopers!{\r}

850
01:20:29,795 --> 01:20:34,391
傘兵部隊!傘兵部隊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Paratroop groups.Those are paratroop groups!{\r}

851
01:23:47,083 --> 01:23:48,311
有沒有新消息？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Anything new?{\r}

852
01:23:48,586 --> 01:23:52,545
瑟堡那邊和平時一樣爆炸聲不斷……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Heavy bombing over Cherbourg as usual, sir...{\r}

853
01:23:52,990 --> 01:23:55,220
……現在接近卡昂了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and now near Caen.{\r}

854
01:23:55,461 --> 01:23:58,157
第六和第八號炮位的線路被切斷……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The lines to Stations 6 and 8 have been cut...{\r}

855
01:23:58,363 --> 01:24:00,490
……但指揮線路還能接通
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...but the direct line is open.{\r}

856
01:24:18,820 --> 01:24:20,685
我在這呆會兒
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'll stay for a while.{\r}

857
01:24:22,324 --> 01:24:25,452
－要咖啡嗎？
－好的,謝謝
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Would you like coffee?
-Yes, thank you.{\r}

858
01:25:07,074 --> 01:25:09,702
看在上帝份上,神父,別再弄出聲音
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}For God's sakes, padre, stop that damn noise.{\r}

859
01:25:09,911 --> 01:25:12,539
抱歉,孩子,我恐怕迷路了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sorry, son. I'm afraid I'm lost.{\r}

860
01:25:12,781 --> 01:25:14,408
有誰不怕？跟我來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, who ain't? Now, come on.{\r}

861
01:26:08,944 --> 01:26:09,968
兩聲「卡嗒」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Two clicks.{\r}

862
01:26:10,279 --> 01:26:12,372
我聽到是兩聲「卡嗒」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I heard two clicks.{\r}

863
01:27:53,562 --> 01:27:54,722
老兄……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Man...{\r}

864
01:27:54,931 --> 01:27:56,853
……很高興見到你們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...am I glad to see you.{\r}

865
01:27:57,633 --> 01:28:00,659
－你們是八十二空降師嗎？
－不,是一○一空降師
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-You guys the 82nd?
-No. This is the 101.{\r}

866
01:28:00,903 --> 01:28:02,234
一○一？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}101?{\r}

867
01:28:02,439 --> 01:28:03,736
那八十二空降師呢？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Where's the 82nd?{\r}

868
01:28:03,941 --> 01:28:07,274
夥計,我們也不知道自己的大部隊在哪
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Look, bud, we don't even know where our own outfit is.{\r}

869
01:28:08,445 --> 01:28:10,970
有人在攻擊對方
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, somebody's shooting at somebody.{\r}

870
01:28:11,216 --> 01:28:12,706
我們去看看戰況
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's us go find this war.{\r}

871
01:28:12,917 --> 01:28:14,248
來吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on.{\r}

872
01:28:44,520 --> 01:28:47,318
也許是英國佬,他們沒有「蟋蟀」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Maybe they're Limeys and ain't got no cricket.{\r}

873
01:28:50,059 --> 01:28:52,015
肯定是自己人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They must be our guys.{\r}

874
01:28:55,633 --> 01:28:57,066
好吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay.{\r}

875
01:29:19,193 --> 01:29:20,785
不
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

876
01:29:36,345 --> 01:29:37,607
嘿
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey.{\r}

877
01:29:38,714 --> 01:29:40,341
嘿,他們是德國人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, they were Germans.{\r}

878
01:29:50,895 --> 01:29:54,991
有數百架飛機從我們兩旁飛過
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hundreds of planes have been flying to my left and right.{\r}

879
01:29:55,233 --> 01:29:56,860
是朝卡昂方向
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Toward Caen.{\r}

880
01:29:57,536 --> 01:29:59,424
是的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes.{\r}

881
01:29:59,872 --> 01:30:05,071
現在飛過瑟堡半島了,一定有情況!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now over the Cherbourg peninsula. Something must be happening!{\r}

882
01:30:05,311 --> 01:30:10,510
什麼情況,普拉斯凱,什麼情況？ 我一點都不明白
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But what, Pluskat, what? I haven't the faintest idea.{\r}

883
01:30:12,385 --> 01:30:16,082
海灘上發現什麼情況沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Has anything been observed on the beaches?{\r}

884
01:30:17,658 --> 01:30:20,422
不,什麼都沒有
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, nothing.{\r}

885
01:30:21,429 --> 01:30:23,761
好的,我會隨時向你報告
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, I'll let you know right away.{\r}

886
01:30:24,065 --> 01:30:25,362
當然
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Of course.{\r}

887
01:30:32,942 --> 01:30:35,399
你肯定是踝骨斷了？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Are you positive that ankle's broken?{\r}

888
01:30:35,612 --> 01:30:37,307
復合骨折,頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Compound fracture, sir.{\r}

889
01:30:37,581 --> 01:30:41,677
把靴子穿回去,繫好靴帶,繫緊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, put the boot back on and lace it up, tight.{\r}

890
01:30:41,919 --> 01:30:43,648
別發火,又不是我弄斷的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't get mad, I didn't break it.{\r}

891
01:30:43,855 --> 01:30:45,652
你也不必用它走路
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And you're not walking on it.{\r}

892
01:30:45,857 --> 01:30:50,180
－你不會是想……
－別再說了,照我說的做
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-You're not going to try--
-Knock it off and do as you're told.{\r}

893
01:31:01,474 --> 01:31:02,463
什麼事？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes?{\r}

894
01:31:02,709 --> 01:31:05,906
Ａ,Ｂ,Ｃ連和我們一樣全走散了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A, B and C Company are scattered all over like we are.{\r}

895
01:31:06,146 --> 01:31:07,477
還有呢
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go on.{\r}

896
01:31:07,682 --> 01:31:11,812
康克林少校落在石牆上摔斷了肩膀,我把他留給衛生員了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Major Conklin landed on a stone wall, broke his shoulder.
I left him with a medic.{\r}

897
01:31:12,119 --> 01:31:13,643
聯絡到Ｆ連沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Any contact with F Company?{\r}

898
01:31:13,854 --> 01:31:17,881
沒有,但他們肯定在前面,聖米爾伊格奡竣閬V
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, but they must be up ahead
in the direction of Sainte-Mere-Eglise.{\r}

899
01:31:18,961 --> 01:31:22,453
別停下,繫好,繫好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, go ahead. Tie it off. Tie it off.{\r}

900
01:31:26,803 --> 01:31:28,430
這是我們的位置
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, here's where we are.{\r}

901
01:31:28,638 --> 01:31:30,560
在沼澤地的北端……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The northern edge of the swamp area...{\r}

902
01:31:30,774 --> 01:31:32,639
……離預定著陸點有五英里
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...five miles from our drop zone.{\r}

903
01:31:32,843 --> 01:31:34,674
五英里
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Five miles.{\r}

904
01:31:35,512 --> 01:31:36,570
－是Ｆ連嗎？
－不,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-F Company?
-No, sir.{\r}

905
01:31:36,814 --> 01:31:38,941
我們四處搜索過了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And we've got scouts all over the place.{\r}

906
01:31:39,184 --> 01:31:41,175
找到了一○一空降師的一隊弟兄
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We even picked up a group from the 101.{\r}

907
01:31:41,419 --> 01:31:45,344
Ｆ連是在領航的第一架飛機上
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}F Company were the first of the lead planes.{\r}

908
01:31:46,425 --> 01:31:48,222
扶我一把
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, give me a hand.{\r}

909
01:31:57,704 --> 01:31:59,433
把我的槍給我
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Can I have my rifle?{\r}

910
01:32:09,685 --> 01:32:11,846
我們朝這個方向走
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, we'll head out this way.{\r}

911
01:32:12,287 --> 01:32:16,917
天亮時我們應該能到達高地或者開闊地
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We ought to reach high ground  and open country by daybreak.{\r}

912
01:32:17,427 --> 01:32:19,691
好了,讓大家分散開來……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right. Have the men spread out...{\r}

913
01:32:19,896 --> 01:32:21,852
……沿途召集走散的弟兄
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...pick up any stragglers they can find.{\r}

914
01:32:22,065 --> 01:32:23,464
－把話傳下去
－是,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Pass the word.
-Right, sir.{\r}

915
01:32:23,701 --> 01:32:26,659
大家分散開,聚攏掉隊的弟兄
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, men, spread out. Pick up stragglers you see.{\r}

916
01:32:26,871 --> 01:32:28,532
把話傳下去
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Pass the word down.{\r}

917
01:32:30,241 --> 01:32:31,606
好了……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right...{\r}

918
01:32:31,910 --> 01:32:33,172
……我們出發
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...Iet's go.{\r}

919
01:32:34,880 --> 01:32:38,407
根據最新的報告,我的看法是……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}From the latest reports, this is how I see it:{\r}

920
01:32:38,651 --> 01:32:41,711
美軍傘兵已經降落在…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}American paratroopers have landed....{\r}

921
01:32:42,855 --> 01:32:44,846
……這
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...here.{\r}

922
01:32:45,558 --> 01:32:47,856
英軍傘兵在這
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}British paratroopers here.{\r}

923
01:32:49,430 --> 01:32:51,091
將會進攻…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The invasion....{\r}

924
01:32:52,232 --> 01:32:54,223
……這
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...here.{\r}

925
01:32:58,339 --> 01:33:00,466
是的,謝謝,彭塞爾
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes. Thank you, Pemsel.{\r}

926
01:33:01,309 --> 01:33:05,006
彭塞爾將軍確信這是入侵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}General Pemsel is convinced that this is the invasion.{\r}

927
01:33:05,247 --> 01:33:10,105
我不同意,我的看法是……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I do not agree with him. This is my conclusion:{\r}

928
01:33:10,387 --> 01:33:13,743
諾曼底只是牽制性攻擊的目標
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Normandy is the objective of a diversionary attack.{\r}

929
01:33:13,957 --> 01:33:16,255
是牽制性攻擊,布魯門特堹S
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A diversionary attack, Blumentritt.{\r}

930
01:33:16,593 --> 01:33:20,484
不是主要攻擊目標,主目標是加萊……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's not the main attack.
That will come at the Pas-de-Calais...{\r}

931
01:33:21,332 --> 01:33:23,129
……早就預料到的地點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...where it was always expected.{\r}

932
01:33:26,772 --> 01:33:28,603
那是我們預料的地點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Where we always expected it.{\r}

933
01:33:29,341 --> 01:33:31,832
但我們不能掉以輕心
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But we can't take any chances.{\r}

934
01:33:32,111 --> 01:33:35,274
立刻出動裝甲預備隊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I want the reserve panzers moved up at once!{\r}

935
01:33:35,615 --> 01:33:38,448
必須經過元首統帥部的同意
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We need approval from the Fuhrer's headquarters.{\r}

936
01:33:38,651 --> 01:33:41,449
他們不敢拒絕我的要求
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They wouldn't dare refuse me!{\r}

937
01:33:41,755 --> 01:33:46,783
打電話給元首統帥部強調這一點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Call the Fuhrer's headquarters and insist.{\r}

938
01:33:46,994 --> 01:33:51,488
強調裝甲部隊要交由我直接指揮
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Insist that the panzers be released to me immediately!{\r}

939
01:33:56,372 --> 01:34:02,060
進攻諾曼底悖離了軍事常規
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}An invasion of Normandy would be against all military logic.{\r}

940
01:34:03,279 --> 01:34:06,203
實在是悖離所有常規
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It would really be against all logic.{\r}

941
01:34:17,410 --> 01:34:20,038
大概就是這些了,各位
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, that about covers it, gentlemen.{\r}

942
01:34:23,184 --> 01:34:25,675
你們大部分以前有過登陸經驗
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Most of you have had your feet wet before:{\r}

943
01:34:26,221 --> 01:34:28,781
敦克爾克,迪耶普,挪威
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Dunkirk, Dieppe, Norway.{\r}

944
01:34:29,025 --> 01:34:31,880
大家都知道被趕下海是指什麼
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And we know what it means to be driven into the sea.{\r}

945
01:34:32,930 --> 01:34:35,057
幾小時後我們要從海上殺回去
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In a few hours we're going back from the sea.{\r}

946
01:34:36,734 --> 01:34:38,895
這次我們要站住腳
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And this time we're going to stay.{\r}

947
01:34:40,339 --> 01:34:44,874
沒有時間來為英格蘭,家園,以及美女而傷感
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There's no time for any sob stuff about...
...England, home and beauty.{\r}

948
01:34:46,447 --> 01:34:50,214
記住,我們的同胞已經受苦受難四年半了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Remember, our people have had a rough time
for four and a half years.{\r}

949
01:34:51,553 --> 01:34:53,714
他們應該贏得最後的勝利
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They've earned the final victory.{\r}

950
01:34:55,960 --> 01:34:57,552
讓我們來實現它
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's give it to them.{\r}

951
01:34:58,862 --> 01:35:01,820
對於軍中的法國戰友,我要說……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And to our French comrades in arms, I say:{\r}

952
01:35:02,100 --> 01:35:03,624
祝你們好運
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Good luck.{\r}

953
01:35:03,903 --> 01:35:05,859
明早,我們要打敗他們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Tomorrow morning, we'll take them.{\r}

954
01:35:14,917 --> 01:35:17,808
請進,泰迪,　　 就這樣吧,中士
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-
Come in, Teddy. That will be all, sergeant.{\r}

955
01:35:16,687 --> 01:35:18,009
請進,泰迪,　　 就這樣吧,中士
(美軍第四步兵師副師長 西奧多·羅斯福准將)

956
01:35:18,009 --> 01:35:22,144
(美軍第四步兵師副師長 西奧多·羅斯福准將)

957
01:35:27,100 --> 01:35:28,931
你一定要寫進報告嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you have to put it in writing?{\r}

958
01:35:29,269 --> 01:35:31,635
不這樣你就不會讓我去
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I knew you wouldn't let me go unless I did.{\r}

959
01:35:31,839 --> 01:35:33,864
你這是給我出難題
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You're putting me on the spot.{\r}

960
01:35:34,109 --> 01:35:36,669
－我不是有意的,塔比
－不是才怪
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-I didn't mean to, Tubby.
-The hell you didn't.{\r}

961
01:35:36,945 --> 01:35:39,709
你都將請求寫進了正式報告
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You put that request in writing, made it official.{\r}

962
01:35:39,949 --> 01:35:42,509
你可是副師長
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You're the assistant division commander.{\r}

963
01:35:42,786 --> 01:35:46,017
所以我應該第一波上岸
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And that's why I'm supposed to go ashore in the first wave.{\r}

964
01:35:46,291 --> 01:35:49,021
我應該去那,你知道的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's where I'm supposed to be.  You know that.{\r}

965
01:35:49,295 --> 01:35:50,922
你對這次行動很重要
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You're important to this operation.{\r}

966
01:35:51,131 --> 01:35:53,793
我們不能在第一天就失去你
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We can't have you knocked off on the first day.{\r}

967
01:35:53,967 --> 01:35:56,299
可那不是真正的理由
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But that's not the real reason.{\r}

968
01:35:56,504 --> 01:36:00,134
是不是因為我父親是美國總統？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Isn't it because my father was president of the United States?{\r}

969
01:36:00,409 --> 01:36:01,808
而且是了不起的總統
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And a great president.{\r}

970
01:36:02,045 --> 01:36:03,808
也是了不起的軍人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}And a great soldier.{\r}

971
01:36:04,047 --> 01:36:07,312
他曾帶領「鐵騎兵」攻下了聖胡安山
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He led the charge of the Rough Riders up San Juan Hill.{\r}

972
01:36:08,353 --> 01:36:11,949
所以現在你想成為第一個登上「猶他海灘」的人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}So now you've got to be the first man ashore on Utah Beach.{\r}

973
01:36:12,158 --> 01:36:15,890
可那是我應該去的地方,這是我的職責
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But that's where I'm supposed to be, Tubby. That's my job.{\r}

974
01:36:22,003 --> 01:36:26,031
而且我和部下一起經歷過所有訓練
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Also, I've been there side by side
with the men all through training.{\r}

975
01:36:26,209 --> 01:36:30,340
他們習慣看到我在場,也有權利期待我在場
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They're used to seeing me there.
They have a right to expect me there.{\r}

976
01:36:30,981 --> 01:36:33,176
不管是不是總統的兒子
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}President's son or not.{\r}

977
01:36:35,887 --> 01:36:37,684
我的請求被拒絕了？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Is my request denied?{\r}

978
01:36:50,107 --> 01:36:51,995
不,你知道不會的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, you know it's not.{\r}

979
01:36:53,745 --> 01:36:57,044
被很不情願地批准了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Request reluctantly approved.{\r}

980
01:36:59,084 --> 01:37:00,608
謝謝,塔比
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thanks, Tubby.{\r}

981
01:37:02,389 --> 01:37:03,617
非常感謝
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thanks a lot.{\r}

982
01:37:05,126 --> 01:37:06,218
那麼……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Say...{\r}

983
01:37:06,427 --> 01:37:08,520
……你的關節炎怎麼樣了？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...how's that arthritis of yours?{\r}

984
01:37:09,097 --> 01:37:10,724
關節炎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Arthritis?{\r}

985
01:37:11,434 --> 01:37:13,891
好幾個月沒發作了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Haven't had a touch in months.{\r}

986
01:37:14,138 --> 01:37:15,469
真是個好消息
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Glad to hear it.{\r}

987
01:37:34,430 --> 01:37:35,624
街道……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The street...{\r}

988
01:37:36,933 --> 01:37:38,230
……橋……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...the bridge...{\r}

989
01:37:39,103 --> 01:37:40,536
……旅館……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...the hotel...{\r}

990
01:37:42,474 --> 01:37:43,930
……賭場
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...the casino.{\r}

991
01:37:45,645 --> 01:37:49,285
(法軍突擊隊指揮官 菲力普·基佛海軍中校)

992
01:37:46,946 --> 01:37:48,743
就是這樣,各位
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's it, gentlemen.{\r}

993
01:37:58,461 --> 01:37:59,792
另外……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}One more thing....{\r}

994
01:38:01,665 --> 01:38:04,657
四年來你們轉戰各方……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You have been fighting everywhere for four years...{\r}

995
01:38:04,969 --> 01:38:10,203
……阿比西尼亞,利比亞,埃及,克里特島……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...in Abyssinia, Libya, Egypt, Crete....{\r}

996
01:38:12,278 --> 01:38:15,338
但這次你們是在法國的領土上作戰……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But this time you are going to fight on French soil...{\r}

997
01:38:15,983 --> 01:38:17,507
……是在我們的土地……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...in our fields...{\r}

998
01:38:18,653 --> 01:38:20,109
……我們的鄉村……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...in our villages...{\r}

999
01:38:22,225 --> 01:38:24,056
……我們同胞的眼皮底下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...under the eyes of our own people.{\r}

1000
01:38:27,466 --> 01:38:31,161
我可不能為這自相矛盾的報告叫醒元首
(阿爾弗雷德·約德爾陸軍上將)
(德國武裝部隊最高統帥部作戰部部長)
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't wake the Fuhrer
on the strength of contradictory reports.{\r}

1001
01:38:30,761 --> 01:38:33,162
(阿爾弗雷德·約德爾陸軍上將)
(德國武裝部隊最高統帥部作戰部部長)

1002
01:38:31,270 --> 01:38:35,094
他吃過鎮靜劑在睡覺,要四點起床
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He was up till four. He took a sedative and then retired.{\r}

1003
01:38:35,109 --> 01:38:38,103
我不能為這些報告吵醒他
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I won't wake him for these reports.{\r}

1004
01:38:38,246 --> 01:38:43,173
最初的報告說傘兵是被擊落飛機上的機組人員
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}First we hear that the paratroopers are shot down plane crews.{\r}

1005
01:38:43,385 --> 01:38:46,513
然後又被說成是橡膠假人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Next they are identified as mechanical dummies.{\r}

1006
01:38:46,723 --> 01:38:50,649
即使報告都是真的而且傘兵已經著陸……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If these reports are true and paratroopers have landed...{\r}

1007
01:38:50,861 --> 01:38:54,525
……也可能只是一次突襲而已
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...it can only be a commando raid.{\r}

1008
01:38:54,767 --> 01:38:59,364
這種理由足以派裝甲部隊前往海岸嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Is that a sufficient reason to send the panzers to the coast?{\r}

1009
01:38:59,706 --> 01:39:04,804
元首醒後我會盡快將這些報告提交給他
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I will submit all reports to the Fuhrer as soon as he awakens.{\r}

1010
01:39:05,814 --> 01:39:07,577
明白了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I understand.{\r}

1011
01:39:09,586 --> 01:39:11,417
約德爾拒絕了請求
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Jodl has turned us down.{\r}

1012
01:39:14,058 --> 01:39:18,689
沒有元首的批准，他不會將裝甲部隊交給我們……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He will not release the panzers
without the Fuhrer's approval...{\r}

1013
01:39:21,234 --> 01:39:24,226
……而元首還在睡覺!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and the Fuhrer is still asleep!{\r}

1014
01:39:25,774 --> 01:39:27,935
要通知馮·龍德施泰特嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Will you tell von Rundstedt?{\r}

1015
01:39:31,347 --> 01:39:32,939
不,暫時不用…….
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, not now....{\r}

1016
01:39:35,319 --> 01:39:37,116
暫時不用
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Not now.{\r}

1017
01:39:38,623 --> 01:39:40,352
謝謝,各位
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you, gentlemen.{\r}

1018
01:39:56,813 --> 01:39:59,236
坐吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sit down.{\r}

1019
01:40:01,252 --> 01:40:03,482
這是歷史性的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}This is history.{\r}

1020
01:40:05,324 --> 01:40:11,987
我們正處在一個歷史性的時刻，我們要輸掉這場戰爭了……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We are living a historical moment.
We are going to lose the war...{\r}

1021
01:40:12,166 --> 01:40:17,025
……就因為偉大的元首吃了一顆安眠藥……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...because the glorious Fuhrer has taken a sleeping pill...{\r}

1022
01:40:18,675 --> 01:40:21,098
……所以不能被吵醒
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and is not to be awakened.{\r}

1023
01:40:22,179 --> 01:40:24,272
真是難以置信
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's unbelievable.{\r}

1024
01:40:24,482 --> 01:40:26,109
想想這一刻,庫爾特
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Think of it, Kurt.{\r}

1025
01:40:27,819 --> 01:40:29,980
永遠別忘了這一刻
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't ever forget it.{\r}

1026
01:40:31,190 --> 01:40:34,148
我們正在見證一件事……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We are witnessing something...{\r}

1027
01:40:34,428 --> 01:40:38,525
……歷史學家會一直說這絕無可能……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...which historians will always say is completely improbable...{\r}

1028
01:40:38,734 --> 01:40:40,429
……但卻千真萬確
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and yet it is true.{\r}

1029
01:40:44,007 --> 01:40:46,999
元首不能被吵醒!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Fuhrer is not to be awakened!{\r}

1030
01:40:48,012 --> 01:40:51,436
有時我真想知道上帝是站在哪一邊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I sometimes wonder whose side God is on.{\r}

1031
01:40:53,453 --> 01:40:54,408
要我……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Can l...{\r}

1032
01:40:55,723 --> 01:40:57,782
……為您拿點什麼來嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...bring you anything, sir?{\r}

1033
01:41:01,663 --> 01:41:05,225
我房間埵酗@瓶上等的干邑白蘭地……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In my room there is a bottle of excellent cognac...{\r}

1034
01:41:05,468 --> 01:41:08,096
……「拿破侖」,還沒開過
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...Napoleon, unopened.{\r}

1035
01:41:08,972 --> 01:41:12,100
我本想留到一個合適的場合再開
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I was even saving it for a fitting occasion.{\r}

1036
01:41:13,112 --> 01:41:17,937
現在算不上合適的場合,可還是拿來再說吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}This isn't exactly the right occasion, but get it anyway.{\r}

1037
01:41:43,584 --> 01:41:45,176
總算天亮了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Daylight at last.{\r}

1038
01:41:47,723 --> 01:41:50,578
又浪費了一整夜!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A whole night wasted again!{\r}

1039
01:41:58,270 --> 01:41:59,464
我的狗呢？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Where's my dog?{\r}

1040
01:41:59,671 --> 01:42:01,764
剛才還在這呢
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He was here a minute ago.{\r}

1041
01:42:07,615 --> 01:42:09,310
最後再看一下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's have one last look.{\r}

1042
01:42:12,989 --> 01:42:14,752
什麼都沒有
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing.{\r}

1043
01:42:15,425 --> 01:42:17,120
連只海鷗都沒……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Not even a seagull....{\r}

1044
01:42:26,873 --> 01:42:28,170
我的天!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}My God!{\r}

1045
01:42:34,817 --> 01:42:36,250
入侵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The invasion.{\r}

1046
01:42:37,754 --> 01:42:39,153
他們來了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They're coming!{\r}

1047
01:42:39,657 --> 01:42:41,613
各就各位!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Everyone to your posts!{\r}

1048
01:42:43,261 --> 01:42:48,052
是入侵!海上至少有五千艘船!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's the invasion!  There must be 5000 ships out there!{\r}

1049
01:42:48,668 --> 01:42:51,159
鎮靜一點,普拉斯凱
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Get hold of yourself, Pluskat.{\r}

1050
01:42:52,973 --> 01:42:56,363
敵軍的船隻連那一半都不到
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The enemy doesn't have even half that many.{\r}

1051
01:42:56,744 --> 01:43:00,772
該死的,自己過來看看吧,你這白癡!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, damn it!  Come and see for yourself, you fool!{\r}

1052
01:43:01,785 --> 01:43:03,412
太驚人了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's amazing.{\r}

1053
01:43:03,687 --> 01:43:06,076
真不敢相信
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's beyond belief.{\r}

1054
01:43:07,359 --> 01:43:11,057
親愛的普拉斯凱,那些船在朝哪開？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}My dear Pluskat, where are these ships heading?{\r}

1055
01:43:11,264 --> 01:43:12,925
衝我這來了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Straight for me!{\r}

1056
01:43:20,442 --> 01:43:24,939
(美國第一集團軍司令 　奧馬爾·佈雷德利中將)

1057
01:43:28,920 --> 01:43:31,616
將軍,兩分鐘之後……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}General, in exactly two minutes...{\r}

1058
01:43:31,824 --> 01:43:34,019
……艦隊就將開火
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...the fleet will open fire.{\r}

1059
01:43:34,827 --> 01:43:38,594
請注意,將軍將發表講話
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Your attention, please.
The admiral has an announcement.{\r}

1060
01:43:39,133 --> 01:43:43,047
(「自由法國」武裝力量　朱雅德海軍少將)

1061
01:43:41,869 --> 01:43:45,830
我們很快將光榮地投身於戰鬥之中
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Soon we will have the honor to be engaged in battle.{\r}

1062
01:43:46,943 --> 01:43:51,870
為了趕走敵人,我們不得不向自己的領土開火
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}To drive the enemy out, we must fire on our homeland.{\r}

1063
01:43:52,751 --> 01:43:54,946
這是自由的代價
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}This is the price of liberty.{\r}

1064
01:43:56,055 --> 01:43:57,386
法蘭西萬歲!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Long live France!{\r}

1065
01:44:26,293 --> 01:44:29,821
他去了,很準時,和往常一樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There he goes, right on time, as usual.{\r}

1066
01:45:20,597 --> 01:45:24,830
他們要上岸了!他們來了!他們來了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They're landing! They're coming! They're coming!{\r}

1067
01:45:33,414 --> 01:45:35,575
我沒瘋,看,他們快上岸了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm not crazy. Look, they're landing!{\r}

1068
01:45:35,883 --> 01:45:38,147
美國人,英國人,還有法國人!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Americans, the English and the French!{\r}

1069
01:46:12,398 --> 01:46:18,493
普拉斯凱,聽到沒有？你怎麼回事？到底怎麼回事？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you hear me? What's the matter with you? What's going on?{\r}

1070
01:46:18,939 --> 01:46:21,499
你一定是聾了!難道……？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You must be deaf! Can't you...?{\r}

1071
01:46:22,643 --> 01:46:26,205
該死的,難道你沒聽見嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Damn it, can't you hear it for yourself?{\r}

1072
01:46:29,652 --> 01:46:33,917
我們正遭到攻擊! 是的,遭到攻擊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're under fire. Yes, under fire!{\r}

1073
01:46:39,198 --> 01:46:43,863
你說盟軍弄不到的那五千艘船……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Those 5000 ships you say the Allies haven't got...{\r}

1074
01:46:44,204 --> 01:46:47,196
……他們弄到了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...well, they've got them!{\r}

1075
01:46:58,723 --> 01:47:00,452
真是太好了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's wonderful!{\r}

1076
01:47:19,917 --> 01:47:21,908
喂？又有什麼事？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes? What is it now?{\r}

1077
01:47:22,220 --> 01:47:23,710
聽我說,「匹普斯」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Listen to me, Pips.{\r}

1078
01:47:23,856 --> 01:47:28,248
入侵已經開始!馬上進入戒備狀態!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The invasion has started!  Put yourself on alert at once!{\r}

1079
01:47:28,528 --> 01:47:32,260
就憑兩架飛機我能幹什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What the hell can I do with only two planes?{\r}

1080
01:47:32,633 --> 01:47:35,022
其他飛機在哪？你這白癡!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Where are the others, you idiots?!{\r}

1081
01:47:35,370 --> 01:47:39,899
普堸,這是命令!馬上準備!明白了嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Priller, that's an order!  Get ready at once! Understand?{\r}

1082
01:47:40,143 --> 01:47:43,067
如果不是太麻煩的話……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If it isn't too much trouble...{\r}

1083
01:47:43,380 --> 01:47:47,613
……能告訴我入侵地點是在哪嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...would you tell me where the invasion is?{\r}

1084
01:47:48,888 --> 01:47:51,777
什麼？諾曼底!真是太妙了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What? Normandy! How delightful!{\r}

1085
01:47:51,992 --> 01:47:56,350
謝了,我忠實的漢斯,這下我們完了!永別了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thanks, my faithful Hans. That's the end for us! So long!{\r}

1086
01:47:57,065 --> 01:48:00,627
在這想睡個好覺真是太難了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's getting very difficult  to get any sleep around here.{\r}

1087
01:48:03,406 --> 01:48:08,640
你準備好長眠不醒吧,入侵已經開始了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Your prospects for a long sleep are excellent.
The invasion has begun.{\r}

1088
01:48:08,914 --> 01:48:13,079
諾曼底,我們要飛往那,我們倆
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Normandy. We're flying there, the two of us.{\r}

1089
01:48:14,287 --> 01:48:15,982
沒有其他人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nobody else is left.{\r}

1090
01:48:17,992 --> 01:48:19,823
我們恐怕是回不來了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't think we're coming back.{\r}

1091
01:48:21,096 --> 01:48:27,457
(「奧馬哈海灘」)
(凌晨六時三十二分)

1092
01:49:16,767 --> 01:49:21,728
開始行動!開始行動!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Move out! Move out!{\r}

1093
01:49:32,054 --> 01:49:33,783
轟炸已經停止
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The shelling has stopped.{\r}

1094
01:49:37,427 --> 01:49:38,724
登陸艇正在接近
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Landing craft approaching.{\r}

1095
01:49:38,963 --> 01:49:43,321
回到你的指揮部,到那堳揮你的部隊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Return to headquarters. Direct your troops from there!{\r}

1096
01:49:43,769 --> 01:49:45,930
登陸艇正在接近海岸!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Landing craft approaching the coast!{\r}

1097
01:49:51,212 --> 01:49:53,476
那些法國混蛋!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Those French bastards!{\r}

1098
01:49:53,715 --> 01:49:55,603
中士!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sergeant!{\r}

1099
01:49:55,851 --> 01:49:59,150
派人把這個送到總部去
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Send this to headquarters by courier.{\r}

1100
01:50:00,791 --> 01:50:05,024
不!你親自去,告訴他們線路被切斷了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No! Take it yourself. Tell them our lines are cut!{\r}

1101
01:50:05,263 --> 01:50:07,219
各位,請過來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Gentlemen, come here please.{\r}

1102
01:50:08,734 --> 01:50:10,929
準備攻擊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Attack!{\r}

1103
01:50:10,904 --> 01:50:12,667
快!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fast!{\r}

1104
01:50:14,375 --> 01:50:16,707
各就各位!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Take your positions!{\r}

1105
01:50:19,348 --> 01:50:21,373
各就各位!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Take your positions!{\r}

1106
01:50:24,154 --> 01:50:26,645
別讓他們靠得太近!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't let them get too close!{\r}

1107
01:50:28,660 --> 01:50:30,321
快!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fast!{\r}

1108
01:50:30,529 --> 01:50:32,326
準備攻擊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Attack!{\r}

1109
01:50:47,851 --> 01:50:51,640
就是那,弟兄們,「奧馬哈海灘」,死神就在前邊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There it is, men.  Omaha Beach, dead ahead.{\r}

1110
01:50:52,558 --> 01:50:53,820
瞄準目標!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Lock on the target!{\r}

1111
01:50:56,796 --> 01:50:58,457
準備行動!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stand by!{\r}

1112
01:52:03,482 --> 01:52:05,746
快離開海灘!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Get off of the beach!{\r}

1113
01:52:05,985 --> 01:52:07,782
我們走!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's go!{\r}

1114
01:52:52,578 --> 01:52:53,738
快,前進!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on, move up!{\r}

1115
01:53:12,704 --> 01:53:13,728
你好,將軍先生
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello, general, sir.{\r}

1116
01:53:13,973 --> 01:53:16,999
－你沒事吧,小子？
－沒事,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Are you all right, boy?
-Yes, sir.{\r}

1117
01:53:17,244 --> 01:53:20,338
你不覺得回去拿上你的槍比較好嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't you think you better go back and get your rifle?{\r}

1118
01:53:20,548 --> 01:53:21,913
去那嗎,長官？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Out there, sir?{\r}

1119
01:53:22,117 --> 01:53:25,041
今天結束以前你肯定用得著它
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You're almost sure to need it before this day is over.{\r}

1120
01:53:26,489 --> 01:53:28,480
是,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir.{\r}

1121
01:53:43,244 --> 01:53:46,077
快!前進!前進
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on! Move on up! Let's go.{\r}

1122
01:53:53,524 --> 01:53:55,788
醫生!醫生!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Medic! Medic!{\r}

1123
01:54:16,620 --> 01:54:19,509
將軍,「奧馬哈海灘」來的第一份報告
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}General, first reports from Omaha, sir.{\r}

1124
01:54:19,725 --> 01:54:21,056
「突擊部隊已經登陸
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"Assault teams have landed.{\r}

1125
01:54:21,293 --> 01:54:24,126
「尚未取得電台聯絡,但是驅逐艦報告說……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No direct radio contact, but destroyers report...{\r}

1126
01:54:24,330 --> 01:54:27,424
「……第一和第二波似乎被困在海灘上
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...first and second waves appear pinned down on the beach.{\r}

1127
01:54:27,668 --> 01:54:30,592
「遭到炮兵和迫擊炮集中攻擊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Concentrated artillery and mortar fire.{\r}

1128
01:54:30,805 --> 01:54:34,572
「第三波前進困難」   傷亡慘重,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Third wave floundering."
Heavy casualties, sir.{\r}

1129
01:54:36,747 --> 01:54:41,538
(「猶他海灘」)
(凌晨六時四十四分)

1130
01:55:33,419 --> 01:55:35,751
等迫擊炮和機槍安靜下來之後……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}When the mortars and machine guns are silenced...{\r}

1131
01:55:35,956 --> 01:55:39,654
……要各單位指揮官在那和我碰頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...have the battalion commanders join me over there.{\r}

1132
01:55:39,894 --> 01:55:41,054
明白
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay.{\r}

1133
01:55:41,262 --> 01:55:43,651
把地圖拿好,艾迪
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hang on to that map case, Eddie.{\r}

1134
01:56:13,771 --> 01:56:15,102
我成功了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I made it.{\r}

1135
01:56:17,710 --> 01:56:18,938
嘿,我成功了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, I made it.{\r}

1136
01:56:19,278 --> 01:56:21,200
看到我撂倒那兩個傢伙沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Did you see me get those two guys?{\r}

1137
01:56:22,916 --> 01:56:24,349
嘿,中士？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, sergeant?{\r}

1138
01:56:28,423 --> 01:56:29,788
中士？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sergeant?{\r}

1139
01:56:31,961 --> 01:56:35,693
據我估計,這不是正確的地點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}As best as I can figure it, this is the wrong beach.{\r}

1140
01:56:35,933 --> 01:56:39,631
我們是在預計登陸點以南一又四份之一英里處
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're a mile and a quarter
south of where we were supposed to land.{\r}

1141
01:56:39,871 --> 01:56:41,600
我們應該在那邊上岸
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We should be up there.{\r}

1142
01:56:41,774 --> 01:56:44,971
指揮船一定是被海面的炮火煙霧弄糊塗了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Control boat must've been confused
by the naval bombardment smoke.{\r}

1143
01:56:45,345 --> 01:56:47,336
我同意,那現在該怎麼辦？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I agree with you, but what will we do now?{\r}

1144
01:56:47,514 --> 01:56:51,110
援軍和重型武器幾分鐘內就會到
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Reinforcements and heavy equipment
will approach in a very few minutes.{\r}

1145
01:56:51,286 --> 01:56:54,380
－我知道,我知道
－如果他們是在正確地點登陸呢？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-I know, I know.
-What if they land at the right beach?{\r}

1146
01:57:03,802 --> 01:57:07,158
不管我們在哪,援兵都得跟著我們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The reinforcements will have to follow us wherever we are.{\r}

1147
01:57:08,908 --> 01:57:10,796
我們就從這兒開始進攻
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're starting the war from right here.{\r}

1148
01:57:11,912 --> 01:57:14,938
－我們向內陸前進
－好的,出發
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Head inland. We're going inland.
-Okay, let's go.{\r}

1149
01:57:32,973 --> 01:57:35,498
跟緊我,照我的樣子做!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Follow me. Do everything I do!{\r}

1150
01:57:39,214 --> 01:57:41,637
好了,出發!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right. Let's go!{\r}

1151
01:57:43,453 --> 01:57:49,051
(「金海灘」,「朱諾海灘」)
(凌晨六時四十分)

1152
01:58:27,743 --> 01:58:30,075
回家了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Head for home!{\r}

1153
01:58:31,648 --> 01:58:35,004
這是德國空軍歷史上最美好的一刻!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Luftwaffe has had its great moment!{\r}

1154
01:58:38,157 --> 01:58:43,443
(「劍海灘」)
(凌晨六時五十三分)

1155
01:58:45,232 --> 01:58:46,597
準備搶灘
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stand by to beach.{\r}

1156
01:58:46,802 --> 01:58:48,861
鄧肯,小心那個據點
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Duncan, take care of that strongpoint.{\r}

1157
01:58:49,572 --> 01:58:52,427
隨時準備行動!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Any minute now. Stand by!{\r}

1158
01:58:52,708 --> 01:58:54,869
讓我們為敦克爾克還以顏色!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Let's give it them back for Dunkirk!{\r}

1159
01:58:55,412 --> 01:58:58,108
敦克爾克,你聽到沒有,克拉夫？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You hear that? Dunkirk. Do you hear it, Clough?{\r}

1160
01:58:58,316 --> 01:59:00,341
那會兒他還乳臭未乾呢
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sure he was at school at the time.{\r}

1161
01:59:02,822 --> 01:59:04,915
來吧,你們這些廢物!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on, you bums!{\r}

1162
01:59:05,692 --> 01:59:09,652
出來,你們這些下流坯! 弗拉納根回來了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come out, you dirty slobs! Flanagan's back!{\r}

1163
01:59:12,835 --> 01:59:15,759
還沒打仗就給淹死,那可太不幸了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The evil of it all. Drowning a man before he fights.{\r}

1164
01:59:15,939 --> 01:59:17,270
哦,來吧!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, come on!{\r}

1165
01:59:52,953 --> 01:59:55,444
車輛繼續前進!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Keep those vehicles moving!{\r}

1166
01:59:55,690 --> 01:59:59,252
憲兵,跟上那些騎自行車的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}MP, chase out those cyclists.{\r}

1167
01:59:59,119 --> 02:00:03,487
(英國皇家海軍海灘指揮官 科林·莫德海軍上校)
離開海灘!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Get off the beach!{\r}

1168
02:00:01,697 --> 02:00:03,824
向內陸前進!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Move inland!{\r}

1169
02:00:06,171 --> 02:00:07,433
你們快點!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on, you lot!{\r}

1170
02:00:07,672 --> 02:00:09,105
趕快
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hurry it up.{\r}

1171
02:00:12,679 --> 02:00:14,271
別在這閒聊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Never mind the blathering!{\r}

1172
02:00:14,514 --> 02:00:16,436
我們要把裝備都安頓好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We must put these down somewhere.{\r}

1173
02:00:16,684 --> 02:00:18,515
你們越早離開海灘……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The sooner you get off the beach...{\r}

1174
02:00:18,686 --> 02:00:21,519
……他們就會越早停止這可惡的炮擊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...the sooner they'll stop this blasted shelling.{\r}

1175
02:00:21,723 --> 02:00:23,748
炮擊會嚇著我的狗!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's very bad for the dog!{\r}

1176
02:00:26,430 --> 02:00:28,261
鎮靜,溫斯頓,鎮靜!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Down, Winston, down!{\r}

1177
02:00:29,333 --> 02:00:31,927
「劍海灘」海灘指揮官,２－Ａ區
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Beach Master Sword, Section 2-A.{\r}

1178
02:00:32,204 --> 02:00:35,469
第三波已準時登陸,後續行動未受阻礙
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Third wave ashore on time. No obstruction to follow-up.{\r}

1179
02:00:35,708 --> 02:00:37,266
待命中
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Standing by.{\r}

1180
02:00:38,712 --> 02:00:40,236
開始行動!
開始行動!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Get going!{\r}

1181
02:00:40,715 --> 02:00:43,275
看在上帝的份上,把它弄出海灘!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}For heaven's sake, get that carrier off the beach!{\r}

1182
02:00:43,484 --> 02:00:46,647
我聽說可以用你的無線電發個簡報
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I was told I could transmit a newsflash on your radio.{\r}

1183
02:00:46,855 --> 02:00:49,312
如果不能開走,就把它搬走!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If you can't drive it, carry it!{\r}

1184
02:00:50,227 --> 02:00:51,353
你說什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You were saying?{\r}

1185
02:00:51,529 --> 02:00:54,157
有人說可以用你的無線電……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I was told I could transmit a newsflash on your--{\r}

1186
02:00:54,333 --> 02:00:57,632
親愛的夥計,我不想顯得不合作……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}My dear fellow, I don't want to appear uncooperative--{\r}

1187
02:00:57,904 --> 02:01:00,464
不錯,我知道媒體的力量
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, I know all about the power of the press.{\r}

1188
02:01:00,740 --> 02:01:04,302
但這條線得忙更重要的事!快點!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But this line happens to be rather busy! Come on!{\r}

1189
02:01:08,451 --> 02:01:10,180
鎮靜,溫斯頓,鎮靜,溫斯頓
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Down, Winston. Down, Winston.{\r}

1190
02:01:13,257 --> 02:01:14,349
他怎麼說？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What did he say?{\r}

1191
02:01:14,625 --> 02:01:16,286
他說不行
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The answer is no.{\r}

1192
02:01:16,527 --> 02:01:18,324
只好用該死的鴿子了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We have to use the damn pigeons.{\r}

1193
02:01:18,530 --> 02:01:20,225
好在我早有準備
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've got these ready.{\r}

1194
02:01:20,799 --> 02:01:22,391
來,綁上去吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Here, clip this on.{\r}

1195
02:01:37,121 --> 02:01:38,611
它們飛錯了方向
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They're going the wrong way.{\r}

1196
02:01:38,856 --> 02:01:40,812
那邊是德國人,白癡!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Not toward the Germans, you idiots!{\r}

1197
02:01:41,059 --> 02:01:44,187
是這邊!是這邊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The other way! The other way!{\r}

1198
02:01:44,397 --> 02:01:46,126
該死的叛徒!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Damned traitors!{\r}

1199
02:01:46,400 --> 02:01:49,028
－牽著它
－你就不能把你的手指拿出來手嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Hold it.
-Can't you get your finger out?{\r}

1200
02:01:49,303 --> 02:01:51,931
－怎麼回事？
－引擎無法啟動,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What's the matter?
-Engine won't start, sir.{\r}

1201
02:01:52,140 --> 02:01:53,767
我想是進了海水
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Full of seawater, I think.{\r}

1202
02:01:55,311 --> 02:01:56,835
我的老祖母經常說……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}My old grandmother used to say...{\r}

1203
02:01:57,047 --> 02:01:59,743
……機械有什麼問題就狠狠揍它
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...anything mechanical, give it a good bash.{\r}

1204
02:02:00,318 --> 02:02:02,548
現在試試
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Try it now.{\r}

1205
02:02:04,823 --> 02:02:05,755
謝謝,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you, sir.{\r}

1206
02:02:05,991 --> 02:02:07,481
走吧,祝你們好運
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Off you go. Good luck.{\r}

1207
02:02:12,433 --> 02:02:13,798
這一下可真有用
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm sure that got it out.{\r}

1208
02:02:15,837 --> 02:02:17,930
這就是我說的厲害角色!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's what I call a hell of a man!{\r}

1209
02:02:18,174 --> 02:02:20,369
我也喜歡他的狗
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Aye, I like his dog too.{\r}

1210
02:02:21,411 --> 02:02:23,208
別在那廢話了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't stand there yapping!{\r}

1211
02:02:23,413 --> 02:02:26,177
這可不是海德公園!是戰場!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}This isn't Hyde Park Corner! The war's over there!{\r}

1212
02:02:28,854 --> 02:02:29,786
跟上!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come along!{\r}

1213
02:02:29,988 --> 02:02:31,250
快!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on!{\r}

1214
02:02:32,192 --> 02:02:35,025
－謝謝
－一切都很順利
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Thank you.
-Everything's going according to plan.{\r}

1215
02:02:35,229 --> 02:02:38,528
等待行動命令,米林,「藍色無邊帽」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stand by to move. Millin, "Blue Bonnet."{\r}

1216
02:02:49,748 --> 02:02:51,943
搞什麼鬼……？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What in God's name...?{\r}

1217
02:02:56,123 --> 02:02:59,912
我的朋友,多麼美好的一天!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Oh, my friends. What a day! What a day!{\r}

1218
02:03:00,228 --> 02:03:02,492
歡迎來到法國!歡迎來到高利維尼蘇!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Welcome to France. Welcome to Colleville!{\r}

1219
02:03:02,731 --> 02:03:04,858
你太好了,真是幸會……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Most kind of you. Very nice to meet you--{\r}

1220
02:03:05,134 --> 02:03:07,261
看,我一直留著這個
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Look at this. I kept it for you all.{\r}

1221
02:03:07,437 --> 02:03:10,270
不過恐怕不夠大家喝的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But I don't think there will be enough for everyone.{\r}

1222
02:03:10,474 --> 02:03:14,571
也許下次吧,我們還另有預約:打仗!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Perhaps next time. We have a previous engagement: the war!{\r}

1223
02:03:15,614 --> 02:03:17,241
不必浪費香檳了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Mustn't lose that champagne!{\r}

1224
02:03:17,617 --> 02:03:20,609
好了,大家集合! 米林,「藍色無邊帽」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, men, fall in! Millin, "Blue Bonnet."{\r}

1225
02:03:22,289 --> 02:03:23,620
再見
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Goodbye.{\r}

1226
02:03:25,260 --> 02:03:28,115
謝謝,小伙子們!謝謝!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you, boys! Thank you!{\r}

1227
02:03:33,871 --> 02:03:36,635
法蘭西萬歲!盟軍萬歲!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Long live France! Long live the Allies!{\r}

1228
02:03:37,843 --> 02:03:39,140
要我說的話……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If you ask me, Flanagan...{\r}

1229
02:03:39,311 --> 02:03:42,769
……這海灘上真有不少古怪的傢伙
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...there's a lot of very peculiar blokes on this beach.{\r}

1230
02:03:44,151 --> 02:03:45,675
歡迎!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Welcome!{\r}

1231
02:03:46,654 --> 02:03:48,281
歡迎大家!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Welcome to you all!{\r}

1232
02:05:39,967 --> 02:05:43,198
謝謝,親愛的,這鞋真漂亮!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Thank you, dear, they're lovely!{\r}

1233
02:05:45,307 --> 02:05:47,969
最好先穿上試試
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Better try them on first.{\r}

1234
02:05:52,450 --> 02:05:53,906
我是隆美爾
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Rommel speaking.{\r}

1235
02:05:54,118 --> 02:05:55,551
早
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Good morning.{\r}

1236
02:05:56,488 --> 02:05:57,853
什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}

1237
02:05:58,490 --> 02:05:59,855
什麼!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What!{\r}

1238
02:06:00,627 --> 02:06:01,924
哪？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Where?{\r}

1239
02:06:02,396 --> 02:06:03,420
諾曼底!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Normandy!{\r}

1240
02:06:04,498 --> 02:06:06,693
他們已經登陸了嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Have they a foothold already?{\r}

1241
02:06:07,202 --> 02:06:09,864
必須阻止他們!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They must be thrown back!{\r}

1242
02:06:10,473 --> 02:06:12,566
裝甲預備隊呢？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What about the panzer reserves?{\r}

1243
02:06:13,677 --> 02:06:17,033
馮·龍德施泰特從元首那獲取指揮權沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Did von Rundstedt obtain their release from the Fuhrer?{\r}

1244
02:06:28,496 --> 02:06:33,093
諾曼底,諾曼底
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Normandy, Normandy.{\r}

1245
02:06:34,170 --> 02:06:35,762
我真是愚蠢!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How stupid of me!{\r}

1246
02:06:36,472 --> 02:06:37,928
愚蠢
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Stupid.{\r}

1247
02:06:39,310 --> 02:06:45,875
(霍克岬據點　清晨七點十一分)

1248
02:06:51,893 --> 02:06:53,292
就是那
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There it is.{\r}

1249
02:07:04,642 --> 02:07:07,304
你是說我們得從那爬上去嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You mean to tell me that's all we gotta climb?{\r}

1250
02:07:07,546 --> 02:07:09,776
還沒有訓練爬的那麼高
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They're not as high as the practice ones.{\r}

1251
02:07:10,049 --> 02:07:11,778
訓練時可沒有炮火
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They wasn't shooting at us then.{\r}

1252
02:07:13,420 --> 02:07:15,809
為什麼不讓空軍或是海軍來幹？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Why can't the Air Force or Navy do this job?{\r}

1253
02:07:16,057 --> 02:07:19,824
從空中看不到懸崖後面掩體內的大炮
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The big guns in bunkers behind the cliff
can't be seen from the air.{\r}

1254
02:07:20,062 --> 02:07:23,293
不幹掉它,它就會幹掉我們海灘上的弟兄
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We knock them out or they'll murder our guys on the beach.{\r}

1255
02:07:23,500 --> 02:07:25,263
是啊,要我說的話……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah, well, if you ask me...{\r}

1256
02:07:25,470 --> 02:07:28,428
……三個老太婆用掃帚就能把我們一掃光
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...three grandmothers with brooms could sweep us off there...{\r}

1257
02:07:28,639 --> 02:07:30,595
……就像從甜餅上轟走蒼蠅一樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...like flies off of a sugar cake.{\r}

1258
02:14:06,085 --> 02:14:07,950
就是它,我們要找的目標
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's it, the one we're after.{\r}

1259
02:15:04,994 --> 02:15:06,291
是空的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's empty.{\r}

1260
02:15:06,763 --> 02:15:10,187
空軍和海軍確實給了他們好看
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Air Force and Navy really plastered this baby.{\r}

1261
02:15:10,501 --> 02:15:11,798
可我沒明白……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But I don't get--{\r}

1262
02:15:12,737 --> 02:15:14,102
這些炮
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The guns.{\r}

1263
02:15:14,807 --> 02:15:16,399
都沒有架好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There ain't no mounts.{\r}

1264
02:15:17,243 --> 02:15:19,404
根本就還沒有安裝過
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They've never even been installed.{\r}

1265
02:15:20,748 --> 02:15:21,942
你是說……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You mean...{\r}

1266
02:15:22,850 --> 02:15:25,774
……我們費了這麼大的勁……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...we come up all this way...{\r}

1267
02:15:26,021 --> 02:15:27,579
……卻只是一場徒勞？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...for nothing?{\r}

1268
02:15:32,696 --> 02:15:34,789
別擔心,你不會有事
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't worry, sarge, you'll be all right.{\r}

1269
02:15:35,066 --> 02:15:37,330
醫生!醫生!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Medic! Medic!{\r}

1270
02:15:38,812 --> 02:15:40,435
(德語) 「請別!」, 「請別!」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"Bitte!", "Bitte!"{\r}

1271
02:15:46,314 --> 02:15:48,737
他嘰哩咕嚕的在說什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I wonder what "Bitte, Bitte" means.{\r}

1272
02:15:59,197 --> 02:16:02,929
你穿著救生衣搞什麼鬼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What the hell are you wearing a life preserver for?{\r}

1273
02:16:03,569 --> 02:16:05,298
我不會游泳
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't swim.{\r}

1274
02:16:13,449 --> 02:16:17,978
諾曼底,真的是諾曼底
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Normandy. It really is Normandy.{\r}

1275
02:16:18,789 --> 02:16:22,749
真是瘋狂,瘋狂,純粹是瘋狂!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}This is madness, madness, sheer madness!{\r}

1276
02:16:24,263 --> 02:16:25,992
什麼事？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What is it?{\r}

1277
02:16:26,266 --> 02:16:30,499
我剛和約德爾將軍通過話,元首已經醒了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I just talked to General Jodl, the Fuhrer is awake.{\r}

1278
02:16:30,738 --> 02:16:36,302
我才不在乎他醒沒醒!裝甲預備隊的事怎麼樣？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't care if he's awake or not!
What about the reserve panzers?{\r}

1279
02:16:37,180 --> 02:16:41,641
元首在大發雷霆……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Fuhrer went into one of his tantrums...{\r}

1280
02:16:42,286 --> 02:16:45,050
……所以沒人敢提任何事
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and no one dared bring up the subject.{\r}

1281
02:16:45,623 --> 02:16:47,784
那就是還處於預備狀態!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They're still held in reserve!{\r}

1282
02:16:48,394 --> 02:16:50,521
是的,元帥
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, field marshal.{\r}

1283
02:16:53,134 --> 02:16:56,523
長官,如果你親自打給元首……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sir, if you would call the Fuhrer yourself...{\r}

1284
02:16:56,939 --> 02:17:00,295
……我相信他會尊重你的看法
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...I am convinced he would respect your views.{\r}

1285
02:17:00,643 --> 02:17:02,076
打給他？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Call him?{\r}

1286
02:17:02,312 --> 02:17:05,167
打給那個波希米亞下士？!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Call that Bohemian corporal?!{\r}

1287
02:17:06,150 --> 02:17:09,483
要我向他奴顏卑膝？!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Crawl on my knees to him?!{\r}

1288
02:17:10,155 --> 02:17:12,783
不!連想都不要想!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No! It is out of the question!{\r}

1289
02:17:16,330 --> 02:17:21,928
「用單調的憂鬱刺傷我的心」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"Wounds my heart with a monotonous languor."{\r}

1290
02:17:22,371 --> 02:17:23,429
什麼意思？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What's that?{\r}

1291
02:17:23,706 --> 02:17:26,971
沒什麼,已經沒有意義了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing, nothing of importance.{\r}

1292
02:17:28,880 --> 02:17:30,575
來,我來幫你
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Here, let me help you.{\r}

1293
02:17:31,750 --> 02:17:34,913
你還好吧,湯姆？快,他們在上邊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You all right, Tom?  Come on, they're up there.{\r}

1294
02:17:39,226 --> 02:17:41,114
－頭
－怎麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Sir.
-Well?{\r}

1295
02:17:41,428 --> 02:17:44,761
史密斯要我轉告你,他的人已準備好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Mr. Smith says to tell you he's stood his men too.{\r}

1296
02:17:45,000 --> 02:17:49,358
德軍帶著機槍和迫擊炮推進到了樹林
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Jerries are moving up into the woods...
...with machine guns and mortars.{\r}

1297
02:17:50,240 --> 02:17:53,266
－要弟兄們做好準備!
－告訴弟兄們……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Tell the men to stand firm!
-Tell the chaps--{\r}

1298
02:17:53,478 --> 02:17:56,572
準備應付敵人下一輪猛烈反攻
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Tell them to expect another counterattack, a heavy one.{\r}

1299
02:18:00,987 --> 02:18:03,012
－拿著,夥計
－謝謝
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Here you are, mate.
-Ta.{\r}

1300
02:18:06,995 --> 02:18:08,724
－什麼事？
－聽
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What's the matter?
-Listen.{\r}

1301
02:18:08,897 --> 02:18:10,785
我聽到了風笛聲
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I thought I heard bagpipes.{\r}

1302
02:18:11,000 --> 02:18:12,865
別傻了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't be daft!{\r}

1303
02:18:21,747 --> 02:18:24,739
我告訴你聽到了風笛聲!是援兵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I told you I heard bagpipes! It's the reinforcements.{\r}

1304
02:18:38,903 --> 02:18:39,961
是拉瓦特!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's Lovat!{\r}

1305
02:18:47,948 --> 02:18:49,279
快!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on!{\r}

1306
02:18:49,850 --> 02:18:51,306
快!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Come on!{\r}

1307
02:19:18,320 --> 02:19:20,447
－抱歉來晚了
－比不來要好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Sorry I'm late.
-Better than never, sir.{\r}

1308
02:19:20,657 --> 02:19:22,056
真高興見到你,希米
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Glad to see you, Shimmy.{\r}

1309
02:19:26,831 --> 02:19:29,994
你們正好被當成了靶子,情況如何？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You boys are right on target. What's the situation?{\r}

1310
02:19:30,202 --> 02:19:33,126
德軍在一英里外的樹林中重新部署
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Jerry's regrouping in the woods, about a mile.{\r}

1311
02:19:33,507 --> 02:19:35,270
有迫擊炮和重機槍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}With mortars and heavy machine guns.{\r}

1312
02:19:35,509 --> 02:19:36,567
有多少？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Numbers?{\r}

1313
02:19:36,844 --> 02:19:40,508
不知道,希米,但似乎正在集結更多兵力
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No idea, Shimmy, but they seem to be moving forward in force.{\r}

1314
02:19:42,384 --> 02:19:44,011
那樣的話,我們就更不能等了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In that case, we won't wait.{\r}

1315
02:19:44,854 --> 02:19:46,219
最好還是行動
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We'd better get moving.{\r}

1316
02:19:46,857 --> 02:19:48,745
好了,我們要穿過去
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, we're going across.{\r}

1317
02:19:48,993 --> 02:19:50,187
－米林!
－是？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Millin!
-Sir?{\r}

1318
02:19:51,029 --> 02:19:52,621
吹「黑熊」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"Black Bear," sir.{\r}

1319
02:19:53,098 --> 02:19:55,362
好了,來吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, come on.{\r}

1320
02:19:55,568 --> 02:19:57,024
都起來!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Everybody up!{\r}

1321
02:19:57,571 --> 02:19:59,027
出發!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}On your feet!{\r}

1322
02:20:05,414 --> 02:20:08,542
是他,他又在吹了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There he goes. He's at it again.{\r}

1323
02:20:08,919 --> 02:20:11,649
你這輩子聽過這麼難聽的聲音嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Ever hear such a bleeding racket in all your life?{\r}

1324
02:20:11,889 --> 02:20:14,619
沒錯,愛爾蘭人吹風笛就是這樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yeah, it takes an Irishman to play the pipes.{\r}

1325
02:20:30,213 --> 02:20:32,340
堅守至援兵到來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold until relieved.{\r}

1326
02:20:32,616 --> 02:20:34,311
堅守至援兵到來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold until relieved.{\r}

1327
02:20:36,788 --> 02:20:41,613
北偏東方向,北偏東方向,聖米爾伊格奡策b這邊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}North by east, north by east. Sainte-Mere-Eglise is that way.{\r}

1328
02:20:42,095 --> 02:20:43,983
有人移動過路標
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Somebody turned that sign around.{\r}

1329
02:20:44,197 --> 02:20:47,895
隊堸ㄓF我就沒人看一下指南針嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Doesn't anybody in this outfit look at a compass besides me?{\r}

1330
02:20:48,336 --> 02:20:49,667
嘿,夥計們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, you guys!{\r}

1331
02:20:49,905 --> 02:20:53,603
過來!過來!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Over here! Over here!{\r}

1332
02:20:54,711 --> 02:20:56,770
過來,跑步!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Over here, on the double.{\r}

1333
02:20:59,451 --> 02:21:01,783
－要把它弄到哪去？
－不知道,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Where you taking that?
-We don't know, sir.{\r}

1334
02:21:02,120 --> 02:21:03,849
我們走錯了路
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We took the wrong road.{\r}

1335
02:21:04,757 --> 02:21:06,486
堶惘酗偵礡H彈藥嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What do you got in here, ammo?{\r}

1336
02:21:06,760 --> 02:21:08,057
是的,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir.{\r}

1337
02:21:08,428 --> 02:21:11,158
－你們是八十二空降師？
－不,長官,是一○一空降師
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-You 82nd?
-No, sir, 101.{\r}

1338
02:21:11,366 --> 02:21:14,028
現在你們歸八十二空降師了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, you're in the 82nd now.{\r}

1339
02:21:15,171 --> 02:21:17,264
－可是長官……
－可是什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-But, sir, we're--
-But what?{\r}

1340
02:21:17,507 --> 02:21:18,872
沒什麼,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing, sir.{\r}

1341
02:21:19,776 --> 02:21:21,641
好了,出發
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, move out.{\r}

1342
02:21:25,284 --> 02:21:27,548
－把路標拔掉!
－是,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Knock that sign down!
-Yes, sir.{\r}

1343
02:21:33,861 --> 02:21:37,684
－上面有東西移動,中校
－臥倒!掩蔽
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Something's moving up there, colonel.
-Hit the dirt! Take cover.{\r}

1344
02:21:40,938 --> 02:21:42,894
是Ａ連的西恩中尉,頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Lieutenant Sheen, sir, A Company.{\r}

1345
02:21:45,243 --> 02:21:47,541
中校,是我!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Colonel, it's me!{\r}

1346
02:21:49,982 --> 02:21:52,405
－你從哪來？
－聖米爾伊格奡
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Where did you come from?
-Sainte-Mere-Eglise.{\r}

1347
02:21:52,686 --> 02:21:55,382
我們控制了主要道路和廣場北側
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We hold the main road and north side of the square.{\r}

1348
02:21:55,690 --> 02:21:58,750
德軍有一個炮兵連在鎮子的另一邊……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Germans have a battery on the other side of the town...{\r}

1349
02:21:58,927 --> 02:22:01,452
－……控制著鄉村地區
－蘭斯少校呢？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-...and command the countryside.
-And Major Lance?{\r}

1350
02:22:01,697 --> 02:22:05,395
－埋伏在廣場的一幢建築
－Ｆ連呢？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Holed up in a building in the square.
-F Company?{\r}

1351
02:22:06,203 --> 02:22:09,765
他們飛過了空降地點,降落到了鎮中心
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They overshot the drop zone
and landed in the middle of the town.{\r}

1352
02:22:10,008 --> 02:22:11,032
繼續說
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go on.{\r}

1353
02:22:11,309 --> 02:22:14,142
那是場惡夢,一場屠殺
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It was a nightmare, sir. A slaughter.{\r}

1354
02:22:14,413 --> 02:22:16,973
在著地之前就被全殲了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They were mowed down before they hit the ground.{\r}

1355
02:22:21,356 --> 02:22:24,018
蘭斯少校派我來和你聯絡
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Major Lance sent me to try and contact you, sir.{\r}

1356
02:22:24,260 --> 02:22:27,822
他想要你批准撤退,然後在鎮外重新部署
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He wants your permission
to pull back and regroup outside of town.{\r}

1357
02:22:30,735 --> 02:22:35,435
不,該死的,我們要拿下聖米爾伊格奡
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, damn it. We came here to take Sainte-Mere-Eglise.{\r}

1358
02:22:35,607 --> 02:22:37,495
要拿下並守住它
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're gonna take it and hold it.{\r}

1359
02:22:38,845 --> 02:22:41,302
跟著中尉,弟兄們
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Follow the lieutenant, gentlemen.{\r}

1360
02:22:52,329 --> 02:22:54,695
－長官
－謝謝
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Sir.
-Thank you.{\r}

1361
02:22:56,034 --> 02:22:59,892
英,加兩軍正從"劍海灘","金海灘"和"朱諾海灘"穩步推進
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}British and Canadians advancing steadily
from Sword, Gold, and Juno.{\r}

1362
02:23:03,276 --> 02:23:05,141
「奧馬哈海灘」有消息嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Anything from Omaha?{\r}

1363
02:23:05,379 --> 02:23:09,578
只收到了第一條消息:激戰,傷亡慘重
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nothing since the first message:
heavy fighting, heavy casualties.{\r}

1364
02:23:09,785 --> 02:23:11,878
長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sir.{\r}

1365
02:23:14,324 --> 02:23:15,552
「奧馬哈海灘」來的？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Omaha?{\r}

1366
02:23:17,428 --> 02:23:18,452
不是
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

1367
02:23:22,101 --> 02:23:25,924
真搞不懂德軍為什麼不投入重型裝甲部隊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't understand
why Jerry hasn't brought his heavy armor into play.{\r}

1368
02:23:26,807 --> 02:23:29,401
除了二十一裝甲師,其餘裝甲師……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All the panzer divisions except the 21st...{\r}

1369
02:23:29,677 --> 02:23:32,202
……似乎都遠在後方
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...seem to be sitting it out in the rear.{\r}

1370
02:23:32,815 --> 02:23:33,839
長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Sir.{\r}

1371
02:23:37,053 --> 02:23:40,717
「法軍突擊隊從『劍海灘』直驅內陸……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"French commandos driving inland from Sword...{\r}

1372
02:23:40,858 --> 02:23:43,281
……已到達烏伊斯特勒昂郊外」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...have reached the outskirts of Ouistreham."{\r}

1373
02:23:43,929 --> 02:23:45,487
烏伊斯特勒昂
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Ouistreham.{\r}

1374
02:26:36,351 --> 02:26:38,012
撤退!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fall back!{\r}

1375
02:26:40,823 --> 02:26:42,415
掩蔽!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Take cover!{\r}

1376
02:26:58,179 --> 02:27:02,276
坦克支援!我們需要坦克支援!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Tank support! We must have tank support!{\r}

1377
02:27:03,586 --> 02:27:09,378
呼叫「巴士底」,呼叫「巴士底」,
我是「溫莎」,請回答,「巴士底」!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello, Bastille. Hello, Batille.
This is Windsor. Come on, Bastille!{\r}

1378
02:27:27,450 --> 02:27:28,781
開火!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fire!{\r}

1379
02:27:36,295 --> 02:27:38,718
注意!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Attention!{\r}

1380
02:27:39,132 --> 02:27:40,565
開火!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fire!{\r}

1381
02:27:44,305 --> 02:27:48,595
呼叫「巴士底」,呼叫「巴士底」,
我是「溫莎」,請回答,「巴士底」!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello, Bastille. Hello, Batille.
This is Windsor. Come on, Bastille!{\r}

1382
02:27:48,844 --> 02:27:50,539
無法取得聯絡!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't get them!{\r}

1383
02:27:50,880 --> 02:27:53,007
繼續試!我們必須有支援!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Keep trying! We must have support!{\r}

1384
02:27:53,650 --> 02:27:58,008
堅守崗位,我去找輛坦克!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold your positions. I'm going for a tank!{\r}

1385
02:27:59,291 --> 02:28:01,748
盡可能給我們掩護!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Give us as much cover as you can!{\r}

1386
02:28:22,187 --> 02:28:24,610
橋,右側!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The bridge, right!{\r}

1387
02:28:49,856 --> 02:28:51,221
開火!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Fire!{\r}

1388
02:28:56,297 --> 02:28:57,662
幹掉那門大炮!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Try for the cannon!{\r}

1389
02:29:03,273 --> 02:29:05,730
把傷員弄出去!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Get the wounded out of here!{\r}

1390
02:29:33,779 --> 02:29:34,803
回去!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Go back!{\r}

1391
02:29:35,649 --> 02:29:37,014
離開這!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Get out of here!{\r}

1392
02:29:38,819 --> 02:29:40,775
不!回去!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No! Go back!{\r}

1393
02:29:56,041 --> 02:29:58,202
你們不能留在這!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You can't stay here!{\r}

1394
02:29:58,444 --> 02:30:01,208
我是修道院的院長嬤嬤
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I am Mother Superior of the convent.{\r}

1395
02:30:01,448 --> 02:30:03,905
這些修女都是合格的護士
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Sisters are qualified nurses.{\r}

1396
02:30:04,185 --> 02:30:09,385
可是夫人…… 我是說,嬤嬤,我們正在打仗!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But madame-- I mean, Mother, we're in the middle of a battle!{\r}

1397
02:30:10,594 --> 02:30:14,361
失陪,照顧傷員
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Excuse me. Take care of the wounded.{\r}

1398
02:30:49,911 --> 02:30:50,935
是坦克!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's a tank!{\r}

1399
02:30:53,649 --> 02:30:55,082
是基佛!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's Kieffer!{\r}

1400
02:31:05,430 --> 02:31:07,489
在另一邊!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}In the other direction!{\r}

1401
02:31:18,414 --> 02:31:21,804
清除碎石!快!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Clear away the debris! Hurry!{\r}

1402
02:31:58,799 --> 02:32:01,188
我們的空軍在哪？!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But where is the Luftwaffe?!{\r}

1403
02:32:01,470 --> 02:32:04,564
－我正在聯繫
－好的,好的,快找吧
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-I'm trying.
-Yeah, yeah, you're trying.{\r}

1404
02:32:12,717 --> 02:32:17,417
英軍攻下了一個灘頭陣地,正向內陸挺進
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The British troops have a beachhead here.
They are moving inland.{\r}

1405
02:32:17,623 --> 02:32:23,517
美軍佔領了聖米爾伊格奡,並切斷了公路
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Americans hold Ste-Mere-Eglise and have cut the highway.{\r}

1406
02:32:23,731 --> 02:32:26,859
我們控制著中央地帶
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We control this center section.{\r}

1407
02:32:27,503 --> 02:32:32,737
美軍雖已登陸,但他們被我軍困住了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Americans have landed but their attack has bogged down.{\r}

1408
02:32:33,377 --> 02:32:36,232
隆美爾說得對
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Rommel is right.{\r}

1409
02:32:36,515 --> 02:32:39,973
如果我們能將他們困在海灘上……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If we can hold them on the beaches...{\r}

1410
02:32:40,219 --> 02:32:42,210
……入侵就會落空
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...the invasion will collapse.{\r}

1411
02:33:17,367 --> 02:33:18,925
醫生!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Medic!{\r}

1412
02:33:19,136 --> 02:33:20,228
這玩意還能用嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That thing still work?{\r}

1413
02:33:20,572 --> 02:33:22,597
是的,長官,偶爾能用
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir, now and then.{\r}

1414
02:33:22,841 --> 02:33:25,332
－有沒有其他灘頭的消息？
－無法直接聯絡
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Anything from the other beaches?
-Not directly.{\r}

1415
02:33:25,611 --> 02:33:29,275
有人收到從驅逐艦發出的閃光信號
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A while ago the sergeant picked up some flashes
from the destroyers.{\r}

1416
02:33:30,083 --> 02:33:34,214
第四師已離開「猶他海灘」向內陸挺進
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The 4th Division is off Utah Beach and moving inland.{\r}

1417
02:33:34,456 --> 02:33:35,821
內陸？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Inland?{\r}

1418
02:33:38,228 --> 02:33:41,356
－第一師呢？
－他們被困住了,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What about the 1st Division?
-They're hung up, sir.{\r}

1419
02:33:41,599 --> 02:33:42,998
和我們一樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Like we are.{\r}

1420
02:33:47,439 --> 02:33:48,804
行動
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Move out.{\r}

1421
02:33:58,253 --> 02:34:00,710
醫生!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Medic!{\r}

1422
02:34:08,132 --> 02:34:10,498
－你有什麼想法？
－想法？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What do you think?
-Think?{\r}

1423
02:34:11,403 --> 02:34:14,702
我們現在死傷至少有一千人
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We must have close to 1000 casualties up to now.{\r}

1424
02:34:14,874 --> 02:34:17,536
要聯絡船隻來接我們嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Do you want me to have the ships start picking us up?{\r}

1425
02:34:18,345 --> 02:34:20,973
－你認為有這樣糟？
－我看不出有其他選擇
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-You think it's that bad?
-I don't see what else to do.{\r}

1426
02:34:21,183 --> 02:34:23,014
我們無法登上山頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We can't get up this hill.{\r}

1427
02:34:23,186 --> 02:34:26,212
如果不能離開海灘,我們會全軍覆沒
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If we don't get off this beach,
we won't have any division left.{\r}

1428
02:34:26,423 --> 02:34:28,152
什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}

1429
02:34:28,358 --> 02:34:30,155
這是我們的部下,湯姆
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}These are our men, Tom.{\r}

1430
02:34:30,361 --> 02:34:34,423
帶他們來難道是為了送死,然後讓剩下的人逃跑嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You think we brought them in
so some die and ask the rest to turn tail?{\r}

1431
02:34:34,667 --> 02:34:37,431
見鬼,不,我們要拿下那個山頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hell, no. We're gonna get up that hill.{\r}

1432
02:34:37,671 --> 02:34:40,231
派人去把「輕騎兵」(突擊隊)給我找來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Find me somebody to speak for the Rangers.{\r}

1433
02:34:40,441 --> 02:34:43,205
海灘背面右側有一條溪谷
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Back down the beach on the right there's a gully.{\r}

1434
02:34:43,544 --> 02:34:48,471
有一支重兵把守,兩側有機槍駐守
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}With a heavily defended roadblock
and machine gun nests on both sides.{\r}

1435
02:34:48,685 --> 02:34:51,779
－如果我們能殺開一條路……
－試過三次了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-If we can blow our way through--
-We've hit it three times.{\r}

1436
02:34:52,022 --> 02:34:54,445
－根本無法接近
－三次不算多
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-We didn't get close.
-Three times isn't enough.{\r}

1437
02:34:54,726 --> 02:34:57,854
我們要再試,能找些工兵來嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're gonna hit it again. Can you find me some engineers?{\r}

1438
02:34:58,064 --> 02:34:59,258
到處都是!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They're all around you!{\r}

1439
02:34:59,498 --> 02:35:01,830
我是指帶有可用裝備的工兵
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I mean engineers with equipment still working.{\r}

1440
02:35:03,704 --> 02:35:05,467
不用和船隻聯絡嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Then I shouldn't radio the ships?{\r}

1441
02:35:05,707 --> 02:35:06,935
不用,該死的!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, damn it!{\r}

1442
02:35:07,208 --> 02:35:11,270
我們需要爆破筒,火箭筒,迫擊炮,剪鉗……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We need bangalore torpedoes, bazookas, mortars, wire cutters...{\r}

1443
02:35:11,448 --> 02:35:14,344
……和所有還能行動的人,傳話下去行嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and every man that can stand. Pass the word, will you?{\r}

1444
02:35:15,953 --> 02:35:17,352
好的,諾爾
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay, Norm.{\r}

1445
02:35:33,976 --> 02:35:36,365
大家都給我聽著
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Now listen to me, all of you.{\r}

1446
02:35:37,247 --> 02:35:39,374
你們要打起精神
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You guys got to snap out of it.{\r}

1447
02:35:39,751 --> 02:35:42,515
我們要離開這向內陸前進
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're getting off of here, and we're going inland.{\r}

1448
02:35:42,788 --> 02:35:45,746
武器呢？將軍,我的弟兄手無寸鐵了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What about weapons, general?  My men lost everything.{\r}

1449
02:35:45,958 --> 02:35:48,347
他們得有裝備才行
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They gotta have something to fight with.{\r}

1450
02:35:48,561 --> 02:35:50,392
解除死傷人員的武裝
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Strip the dead and the wounded.{\r}

1451
02:35:50,631 --> 02:35:52,622
凡是可用的武器都帶上
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Pick up anything that'll shoot.{\r}

1452
02:35:52,800 --> 02:35:55,496
用不著我說,你們都清楚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't have to tell you the score, you all know it.{\r}

1453
02:35:55,771 --> 02:35:58,660
只有兩種人能留在海灘上
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Only two kinds of people are gonna stay on this beach:{\r}

1454
02:35:58,875 --> 02:36:02,835
已經死掉的和將會死掉的,都給我起來!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Those that are already dead and those that will die.
Get off your butts!{\r}

1455
02:36:03,047 --> 02:36:05,777
你們是身經百戰的二十九師!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You guys are the fighting 29th!{\r}

1456
02:36:23,340 --> 02:36:25,069
我看過海軍的報告
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've looked at the naval reports.{\r}

1457
02:36:25,309 --> 02:36:26,401
怎麼樣？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes?{\r}

1458
02:36:27,211 --> 02:36:31,342
據驅逐艦傳來的報告說,「奧馬哈海灘」兇多吉少
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}According to reports from the offshore destroyers,
Omaha is a shambles.{\r}

1459
02:36:31,818 --> 02:36:34,548
沒有跡象……  報告原文是:
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}There's no evidence--
To quote the report exactly:{\r}

1460
02:36:34,788 --> 02:36:39,078
「海灘上觀察不到有任何活動的跡象」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"There is no evidence of any movement
that can be observed off the beach."{\r}

1461
02:36:41,062 --> 02:36:42,893
我還是再看一遍比較好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'd better have a look through these.{\r}

1462
02:36:46,403 --> 02:36:47,936
艾克對此有何反應？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How is lke taking it?{\r}

1463
02:36:48,138 --> 02:36:51,927
和其他人一樣,長官,在焦急等待
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Like everybody else, sir. Hanging on by his fingernails.{\r}

1464
02:36:54,346 --> 02:36:58,078
不,不!我們必須照方案六重新部署!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No, no! We must regroup according to Plan Six!{\r}

1465
02:37:02,324 --> 02:37:06,216
喂？喂？能聽到嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hello? Hello? Can you hear me?{\r}

1466
02:37:06,529 --> 02:37:09,919
我是說我們必須照方案六重新部署!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I said we must regroup according to Plan Six.{\r}

1467
02:37:11,035 --> 02:37:12,764
廢話!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Nonsense!{\r}

1468
02:37:13,038 --> 02:37:16,303
如果裝甲師能來還不算太晚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If the panzers arrive, we still have time to use them.{\r}

1469
02:37:20,047 --> 02:37:22,072
我們乘車去海岸!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll drive to the coast!{\r}

1470
02:37:22,549 --> 02:37:24,380
要銷毀文件嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Shall we remove the files?{\r}

1471
02:37:24,786 --> 02:37:29,383
這我不在乎!我要馬上去前線,去諾曼底!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't care! I want to get to the front at once, to Normandy!{\r}

1472
02:37:29,591 --> 02:37:30,615
是,將軍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, general.{\r}

1473
02:37:58,062 --> 02:38:00,428
－其他人在哪？
－什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Where is everybody?
-What?{\r}

1474
02:38:02,835 --> 02:38:05,030
我說其他人在哪？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I said, where is everybody?{\r}

1475
02:38:07,474 --> 02:38:09,430
我聽不見
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I can't hear you.{\r}

1476
02:38:10,678 --> 02:38:12,543
是那口大鐘
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's them bells.{\r}

1477
02:38:12,781 --> 02:38:15,636
在我耳朵媗T了足有十個鐘頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've had them in my ears for 10 hours.{\r}

1478
02:38:15,852 --> 02:38:18,844
叮－當,叮－當
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Ding-dong, ding-dong.{\r}

1479
02:38:20,691 --> 02:38:22,818
嘿,中士,蘭斯少校在哪？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hey, sergeant, where's Major Lance?{\r}

1480
02:38:23,027 --> 02:38:25,484
指揮所轉移到了那幢建築,他在那
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We moved the CP to that building. The major's there.{\r}

1481
02:38:25,731 --> 02:38:27,596
去找他,中校來了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Get him, the colonel's here.{\r}

1482
02:38:29,102 --> 02:38:30,262
什麼？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What?{\r}

1483
02:38:32,272 --> 02:38:34,263
停下!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Hold it!{\r}

1484
02:38:44,088 --> 02:38:46,352
中校,見到你太好了!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Colonel, am I glad to see you!{\r}

1485
02:38:47,526 --> 02:38:50,586
那些屍體,把那些屍體弄下來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Those bodies. Get those bodies down.{\r}

1486
02:38:50,863 --> 02:38:53,252
怎麼讓他們留在上面？取下來!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Why are you leaving them up there?  Get them down!{\r}

1487
02:38:53,534 --> 02:38:55,229
我們一直處在火力之下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But we've been under fire, sir.{\r}

1488
02:38:55,536 --> 02:38:57,458
我知道,但我不管!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I know you have, but I don't care!{\r}

1489
02:38:57,705 --> 02:38:59,900
快取下!取下!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Get them down! Down!{\r}

1490
02:39:00,276 --> 02:39:04,236
－我不想讓弟兄們留在那
－帶一隊人去辦
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-I don't want those boys left there.
-Take a detail and cut them down.{\r}

1491
02:39:04,548 --> 02:39:06,311
－馬上去!
－是,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-At once!
-Yes, sir.{\r}

1492
02:39:10,556 --> 02:39:15,221
我們的部隊和海上的軍隊之間有接應嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Has there been a linkup
between our forces and the troops from the sea?{\r}

1493
02:39:15,395 --> 02:39:19,628
不知道,少校,我連他們是否已經登陸都不知道
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I don't know, major.
I don't even know if the landings took place.{\r}

1494
02:39:19,867 --> 02:39:24,623
我只知道必須守住這個鎮直到接應部隊前來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}But I am sure we're gonna hold this town
until the linkup does come.{\r}

1495
02:39:24,907 --> 02:39:29,402
無論是今天,明天,還是要等到地獄凍結
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Whenever that is, today, tomorrow, till hell freezes over.{\r}

1496
02:39:31,081 --> 02:39:32,946
哪怕只看在他們份上
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}For their sake, if for no other reason.{\r}

1497
02:39:33,151 --> 02:39:35,642
告訴我敵人的位置在哪
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Show me the enemy positions.{\r}

1498
02:39:35,854 --> 02:39:38,743
是,長官,德國人的據點就在那
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, sir, the Germans' strong point is right there.{\r}

1499
02:39:38,959 --> 02:39:41,792
就在那邊的山上,還沒有坦克
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's over there on the hill. They've got no tanks yet.{\r}

1500
02:39:42,096 --> 02:39:46,090
他們在公路上方佈置了重炮,迫擊炮和機槍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}They've got heavy guns, mortars and machine gun
positions at the top of that road.{\r}

1501
02:39:46,268 --> 02:39:48,532
你有多少人？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}How many men have you got?{\r}

1502
02:39:48,705 --> 02:39:49,797
不夠
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Not enough.{\r}

1503
02:39:50,106 --> 02:39:53,929
上尉和威爾遜中尉帶Ａ連去增援蘭斯少校
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Captain and Lieutenant Wilson will take A Company
and reinforce Major Lance.{\r}

1504
02:39:54,612 --> 02:39:59,346
其他的人跟我們一起向公路前進
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The rest of the command will follow us straight up that road.{\r}

1505
02:40:00,653 --> 02:40:01,677
祝你好運,少校
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Good luck, major.{\r}

1506
02:40:01,954 --> 02:40:04,479
好的,Ａ連,離隊
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, A Company, fall out.{\r}

1507
02:40:04,725 --> 02:40:06,818
－二等兵
－是,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Private.
-Yes, sir.{\r}

1508
02:40:06,995 --> 02:40:08,189
真是地獄戰場
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's a hell of a war.{\r}

1509
02:40:08,396 --> 02:40:10,956
我願意和您並肩作戰, 中校
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It's a privilege to serve with you, colonel.{\r}

1510
02:40:11,166 --> 02:40:15,194
但願我們能完成我們來此的目的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, God willing, we'll do what we came here to do.{\r}

1511
02:40:15,405 --> 02:40:17,293
準備好了,頭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Ready, sir.{\r}

1512
02:40:17,642 --> 02:40:19,303
出發!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Move out!{\r}

1513
02:40:29,523 --> 02:40:33,085
老頭肯定是從昨天開始改變的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The old man sure has changed since yesterday.{\r}

1514
02:40:39,002 --> 02:40:41,266
也可能是我們改變了……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Or maybe it's just that we've changed...{\r}

1515
02:40:42,373 --> 02:40:44,000
……從昨天開始
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...since yesterday.{\r}

1516
02:40:51,752 --> 02:40:54,380
拉瓦特已率突擊隊抵達大橋
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Lovat and his commandos have reached the bridge.{\r}

1517
02:40:55,490 --> 02:40:56,923
鮑勃,你在聽嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Bob, did you hear?{\r}

1518
02:40:57,659 --> 02:40:59,183
是的,我在聽
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, I heard.{\r}

1519
02:41:00,663 --> 02:41:05,124
「聖米爾伊格奡竣w被八十二空降師佔領」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}"Sainte-Mere-Eglise captured by units of the 82nd Airborne."{\r}

1520
02:41:06,971 --> 02:41:09,804
「一○一空降師正在『猶他海灘』推進」
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}" 101 Airborne driving on Utah."{\r}

1521
02:41:10,042 --> 02:41:12,738
很好,很好
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}That's good. Good.{\r}

1522
02:41:13,180 --> 02:41:18,073
是的,是不錯，
但如果不能從「奧馬哈海灘」脫身就毫無意義,這我們都清楚
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, but if we can't get off Omaha it doesn't mean a damn. We know it.{\r}

1523
02:41:18,286 --> 02:41:22,981
我們拿下了兩處灘頭陣地,一處是英軍區,一處是"猶他海灘"
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We'll have two cut-off beachheads,
one in British zone and one at Utah.
Yes...{\r}

1524
02:41:23,326 --> 02:41:25,487
……但是中間是德軍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...and the Germans in between.{\r}

1525
02:41:40,982 --> 02:41:42,813
你們是工兵嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You guys engineers?{\r}

1526
02:41:44,253 --> 02:41:45,982
是,長官,第二九九特種工兵營
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir, 299th.{\r}

1527
02:41:46,222 --> 02:41:49,111
指揮官呢？這堨挼眴t責？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Where are your officers? Who's in charge here?{\r}

1528
02:41:49,727 --> 02:41:52,218
我想是由我負責,長官,指揮官都不在
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I guess I am, sir.  None of our officers made it in.{\r}

1529
02:41:52,430 --> 02:41:54,455
裝備呢？爆破筒能用嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}What about your equipment? Those torpedoes work?{\r}

1530
02:41:54,733 --> 02:41:56,655
是的,長官,當然能用!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir, we'll make them work!{\r}

1531
02:41:58,037 --> 02:42:00,733
－你叫什麼,中士？
－Ｊ·Ｈ·弗勒,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-What's your name, sergeant?
-It's Fuller, sir, John H.{\r}

1532
02:42:01,008 --> 02:42:04,501
現在起你是弗勒少尉,不管你願不願意
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You're Lieutenant Fuller from now on,
whether you like it or not.{\r}

1533
02:42:07,083 --> 02:42:10,611
派人帶上爆破筒去溪谷底部
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You send some men down to the foot of that gully with those torpedoes.{\r}

1534
02:42:10,888 --> 02:42:14,620
－你和其餘的人跟我來
－是,長官!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-You and the rest of the men follow me.
-Yes, sir!{\r}

1535
02:42:14,893 --> 02:42:18,421
好了,弟兄們!帶上裝備離開這
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, men! Let's move that equipment down here.{\r}

1536
02:42:24,839 --> 02:42:28,263
－我有支槍,長官
－很好,小伙子!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-I got a rifle, sir.
-Well, good for you, son!{\r}

1537
02:42:28,911 --> 02:42:30,401
「輕騎兵」在待命,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}The Rangers are ready, general.{\r}

1538
02:42:30,579 --> 02:42:32,968
好的,少校,叫他們出發
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay, major, move them out.{\r}

1539
02:42:33,149 --> 02:42:35,879
上尉,讓他們出發
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Captain, move them up.{\r}

1540
02:42:36,120 --> 02:42:38,315
出發!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Move them up!{\r}

1541
02:42:40,525 --> 02:42:42,390
－什麼事？
－我們準備好了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-Well, Tom?
-We're ready.{\r}

1542
02:42:42,628 --> 02:42:44,255
一切已準備就緒
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}As ready as we'll ever be.{\r}

1543
02:42:44,497 --> 02:42:47,330
會成功的,一定會成功
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}It'll work. It's got to work.{\r}

1544
02:42:49,103 --> 02:42:53,495
我們在這會被幹掉!
倒不如推進到內陸再死!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We're getting murdered here!
We might as well move inland and get murdered!{\r}

1545
02:42:57,514 --> 02:42:59,072
－準備好了？
－是,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}-You ready?
-Yes, sir.{\r}

1546
02:42:59,317 --> 02:43:01,945
給我把那個路障清除掉
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You're gonna blow that roadblock for me.{\r}

1547
02:43:02,186 --> 02:43:04,711
收到信號立刻行動,懂嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}When I give the word everything pops at once. Okay?{\r}

1548
02:43:04,957 --> 02:43:07,323
是,長官
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Yes, sir.{\r}

1549
02:43:33,460 --> 02:43:37,090
我們先要用爆破筒在鐵絲網上炸個洞
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}First, we gotta blow a hole through that wire with bangalores.{\r}

1550
02:43:37,366 --> 02:43:41,428
能成功的話就把所有炸藥填到牆底下
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}If that works, we'll pack everything we've got into that wall.{\r}

1551
02:43:42,405 --> 02:43:43,963
好了,上!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, let's go!{\r}

1552
02:46:43,738 --> 02:46:48,335
行了,衝啊!沖!沖!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}All right, let's go! Go! Go!{\r}

1553
02:47:47,688 --> 02:47:51,250
我們必須離開,公路幹線遭到了空襲
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}We must leave. The main highway is under aerial attack.{\r}

1554
02:47:51,492 --> 02:47:53,187
不用你說!
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You don't say!{\r}

1555
02:49:30,721 --> 02:49:32,177
別擔心,美國佬
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Don't worry, Yank.{\r}

1556
02:49:37,363 --> 02:49:38,421
他死了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He's dead.{\r}

1557
02:50:00,025 --> 02:50:03,848
給我一支煙,我想抽煙想得要命
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Give me a cigarette. I'm dying for a cigarette.{\r}

1558
02:50:11,739 --> 02:50:13,172
傷得很重嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You hurt bad?{\r}

1559
02:50:17,113 --> 02:50:19,104
夜堻Q擊落了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Shot down during the night.{\r}

1560
02:50:23,055 --> 02:50:27,220
他想看我死了沒有,被我幹掉了……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He was gonna make sure of me, but I got him...{\r}

1561
02:50:27,627 --> 02:50:29,083
……用這個
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...with this.{\r}

1562
02:50:39,776 --> 02:50:43,702
你殺過人沒有？我是指,面對面地？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You ever killed a man? I mean, face to face?{\r}

1563
02:50:45,583 --> 02:50:47,608
沒有
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

1564
02:50:47,786 --> 02:50:51,450
我也沒有,面對面地
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Neither had l, face to face.{\r}

1565
02:50:54,962 --> 02:50:57,419
我一直坐在這看著他
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I've been sitting here looking at him.{\r}

1566
02:50:59,101 --> 02:51:01,763
你發現他有什麼特別之處沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Have you noticed anything peculiar about him?{\r}

1567
02:51:11,684 --> 02:51:13,709
沒有
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}No.{\r}

1568
02:51:14,621 --> 02:51:16,248
他的靴子……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He's got his boots...{\r}

1569
02:51:16,623 --> 02:51:18,750
……穿錯了腳
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...on the wrong feet.{\r}

1570
02:51:26,302 --> 02:51:28,224
他一定非常匆忙對吧？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He must have been in a big hurry, huh?{\r}

1571
02:51:30,474 --> 02:51:31,702
嚴重嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Is it bad?{\r}

1572
02:51:34,646 --> 02:51:36,477
裂了個大口子……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Split wide open...{\r}

1573
02:51:37,683 --> 02:51:39,878
……從胯部一直到膝蓋
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...from the crotch to the knee.{\r}

1574
02:51:40,654 --> 02:51:44,580
有個軍醫來過,給我注射了嗎啡
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}A medic came along and gave me a shot of morphine.{\r}

1575
02:51:47,363 --> 02:51:49,923
但願他在藥效失去前回來
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I hope he'll be back before it wears off.{\r}

1576
02:51:51,168 --> 02:51:52,499
他說他會的
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He said he would.{\r}

1577
02:51:55,439 --> 02:51:57,134
他替你縫合沒有？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Did he sew you up?{\r}

1578
02:52:00,980 --> 02:52:06,009
他上岸時把大部分器材都弄丟了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Well, when he came ashore he lost most of his equipment.{\r}

1579
02:52:07,689 --> 02:52:09,520
所以他縫合時只能……
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}So he pinned it together...{\r}

1580
02:52:10,560 --> 02:52:12,619
……用別針
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}...with safety pins.{\r}

1581
02:52:24,277 --> 02:52:25,835
天就快黑了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Getting on toward night.{\r}

1582
02:52:34,023 --> 02:52:35,285
你知道嗎？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You know something?{\r}

1583
02:52:36,826 --> 02:52:38,817
我整天都沒開過一槍
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I haven't fired my gun all day.{\r}

1584
02:52:39,330 --> 02:52:43,119
我不斷聽到槍聲,
但每次等我趕到,就沒人了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I keep hearing shooting,
but every time I get there, everybody's gone.{\r}

1585
02:52:47,073 --> 02:52:48,506
真滑稽,是吧？
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Funny, isn't it?{\r}

1586
02:52:49,876 --> 02:52:51,104
他死了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}He's dead.{\r}

1587
02:52:52,380 --> 02:52:54,007
我瘸了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I'm crippled.{\r}

1588
02:52:55,251 --> 02:52:56,843
你迷路了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}You're lost.{\r}

1589
02:52:59,389 --> 02:53:01,277
我猜它一直都是這樣
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I suppose it's always like that.{\r}

1590
02:53:03,261 --> 02:53:04,785
我是指戰爭
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I mean war.{\r}

1591
02:53:12,273 --> 02:53:14,104
我想知道誰贏了
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}I wonder who won.{\r}

1592
02:53:57,030 --> 02:53:59,692
好了,送我上山,小伙子
{\fnTimes New Roman\fscx70\fscy70\1c&H00FFFF&}Okay, run me up the hill, son.{\r}

